results_0_description: Royal YAAAAAAAS, FKA Les Dauphins, FKA I hate you, changes their name along with AJ Reusts mood swings.  I know where you can get some Lithium if y’all need it. This game would have been considered intense had it not been for the game that must not be named. The first half Royal backed that YAS up into a tie with the Eggplant Emoji’s. On offense the Marks, J & H, both had a touchdown for Purple along with a try ran in by QB1 Dave S. DeWayne A. and Sam B. had the sixers for Royal and with a try ran in by QB2 AJ. Defensively, Braden B. had two sacks for Purple, and Levert added an int for his YAS of the half. The second half was just as close with a game tying drive by Purple stopped by Dewayne A. with a game sealing interception tapping both feet somewhere on the field. Purple showed their finest with an added sack from Braden and int from Chris H., but Royals came up with three big defensive stops in the end: A fourth down stop and two ints by Dewayne A. Eggplant Emojis left the field with the Lorde’s voice echoing in their heads, “You’ll never be Royals”.
results_1_description: The DCGFFL is all about Sportsmanship! “Get off the bench and get into the game” is our league motto. While we might not have any Sportsmanship Award nominees in the running after this game, there's always next week. If all else fails we’ll just give it to Bryan Sanders again.  Because that makes just as much sense as last year. Maroon lost despite great offensive efforts from Austin and Smiffy. Charcoal won thanks to the receiving efforts of Morse and qb play of Adam Robbins.  Congrats Charcoal!
results_2_description: The athletic heroics of Jordan Anderson weren't enough to plague the Ash team and a superb game from Kyle Mckinney, Scott G., James R. and Seaton. Jordan had 24 points out of 26 on the day for Black, but the combined efforts of Ash shoved it in the mouths of the plague by putting up 39 points. Brian Hotchkiss turned out to be the Plague Black has warned us about.
results_3_description: Yo (t)HOTS, delete Grindr from y'alls phones and start paying attention to the game.  Vegas had six and won with their back up QB. The first half was a boring affair with an int from Andy and a sack by Derrick from Red. Vegas managed a lone TD and an int by Dameron.  The second half Vegas went all in on offense AND defense notching three ints: Matt(2) & another for Dameron, as well as three touchdowns to Markco (2) and Dameron. Red's Miles managed a score before Dameron walked off the field yelling and wagging his finger, "BITCH I TOLD Y'ALL NOT TO COME FOR US, I TOLD Y'ALL. THAT WAS WITH SIX Y'ALL. WE ONLY HAD SIX Y'ALL".
results_4_description: The most racially tone deaf team name lost again on Sunday. We Love You Long Lime missed the mark on Asian American sensitivity as well as in the win column.  The first half was separated by one extra point with Lime and Safety Orange trading two touchdowns a piece, Tim A. and Captain Barry M. for Safety and Nick B. and Josh R. for Lime. Paddy Mac logged the 2 point conversion for Safety while Lime only managed a one pointer from QB Marvin. The second half fell in the Blumpkin's favor seeing two scores to Lime's one. Josh R came up big for all 7 points for lime, but Barry M and Tony S. logged two scores for the Blumpkins and Max R. sealed the deal with an extra point return for 2.
results_5_description: Lime won this game by a sizeable margin.  It looks like CharredHoles lit themselves on fire in the second half and let Marvin W. completely take this game over.  People totally did things on both sides of the ball including QB Marvin Washington on Lime and Cam B. on Charcoal but this maze of a score card leads me to believe the referees were so bored by this trouncing they decided to give up around 8 minutes into the first half.
results_6_description: Royal and Maroon were able to keep their composure and play a full game with no incident. Dewayne ruled the stats sheet for Royal with four touchdowns.  Maroon had no answer to him. Dewayne's points alone weren't enough to seal the victory as Maroon had 27 points of their own, but Smiffy, Austin, Ken & Brandon couldnt uncut their way past the scoring line on Royal with Mike Z, AJ and others combing to add an additional 11.  Yas Qweens ya'll kept Maroon defeated on your way to having the most wins in the league.
results_7_description: WOOOOeeeEE! Both of these teams could score at will. Blumpkins got off their porcelain throne for just long enough to be out shot by Gold 41-37. Gold's QB Sheerod spread the ball around hitting six team mates for scores and tries. The Blumpkins shared the wealth themselves having four teammates log touchdowns. In the end Sheerod had the hottest hand and the game of no defense came to a halt.
results_8_description: Close but no cigar Red. Peach Perfect was Peach Adequate in their first win.
results_9_description: Sexual chocolate took advantage of the sasters of Alpha White in the first half Or should I say Kostyk took advantage of their team: he had an int, a td, and a one point try. Larry W. returned the favor in the second scoring two tds with a murtaugh try after an Earl A. interception, but Brown spread their sexual healing across the field with scores and tries from Sean K., Alex H. and two sacks from Matt N.
results_10_description: Gay Super Bowl Participant QB Adam Martin decided to show up again this week. NINE kelly players showed up on the scorecard this week proving that perhaps Adam Martin knows how to find an open man. Just click on their team page thats who scored 5 tds and had sacks. Pacific Blue only score twice, once in each half. It was adorable.
results_11_description: Forest forgot to cheat. They also forgot to win. Bryan Sanders you listened to my advice last week and you didnt show up to this game! To their credit The Cream Pies stuck this one out to the end. Nothing on the scorecard int the first half and an explosion of points in the second converting three touchdowns and all three conversions.  Forest could only manage one td each half, one to Captain Joe H. the other to some straight person I don't remember because they have such a forgettable face, body and personality. They also converted their tries but it wasn't quite enough to stop the spector of Andy Allen (who was on the winning side despite not appearing on the scorecard once) from edging them out. 21-14 win for Neon Yellow! Congrats Long & JJ, enjoy this last win of the season until you play Red in a play in game.
results_12_description: Another game another routing for the Sky Curious Baby Blue Team.  Strokes of Midnight only managed one score off a missed flag pull at the end of the first half. Midnight drove the field but nearly always ended their drive with a Clevenger interception or pass break up to turn over on downs. Jack B, grindred down the field, scruffed up touchdown after touchdown and gay tindered the ball into the hands of his receivers. Jason, Aras, William & Tom all logged sacks against a floundering offense that left the second consecutive mercy rule for Baby Blue at 34-6.
results_13_description: EESH. Power Blue had a garbage touchdown in the second half, otherwise it was all Fuschia and Jim C. Sean B had a wonderful game for an old lady locking down 13 points and an interception. Captain Adam S., Michelle, Scott and Jim did everything else. Damn this game was boring.

results_0_description: Red (T)HOTS had 7 sacks, 2 interceptions and 0 quarterbacks. Walking zombie Earl Armstrong couldn’t get out of Derrick J.’s clutches.  You’d think Derrick was one of our straight allies with how good he is with reaching for the snatch. Nolan picked off a floundering white offense twice in the first half as well. But unfortunately for those thirsty thots, they turned out to be red from blushing during their first loss. The first half had maybe one first down in the first five drives from each team.  Earl finally put a drive together a scoring drive finding Will C. in the end zone and rushing in himself for the conversion towards the end of the first.  The second half added another TD caught by Matt M, and the game was put away with an int from Larry W. This group of sorority sasters is lucky Red relied on the QB talents of Captain Derrick and newbie Andy for the game.  They eked out a win and are looking towards next week.
results_1_description: Peach Perfect started their day more fuzzy than fresh failing to score in the first half of this match-up with the Black Plague. The Black Plague who’s favorite NFL team is the Redskins, because they also have a racist name, were able to capitalize on Peach’s slow start with a touchdown to Mike Hess from Haskell Noyes. Orange’s Jared kept the game close with an interception. The second half saw Jordan Anderson explode and fend off an offensive push by the Peaches of Perfect. Two scores later Black wins with a score of 18-15.  The Brothers Cline connected for their first touchdown of the season. The smaller one connected with Jared twice for a score and a conversion. Matt ran in a 2 pointer, coming so close to the win. The plague didn’t even need extra points because they are straight sickening. Peach Perfect was gagging from the performance they just witnessed.
results_2_description: The Cookie Monsters, which I hope is an Empire TV Show joke, tallied six interceptions through this game against all three QB’s RJ, Captain Joe Heron & Bryan Sanders: Greg C. had four, one brought back for a touchdown, Rudy B. had two.  Forest Green were able to pick off Gurg Kinterdean’s passes four times of their own: Kyle M., CJ, Rj & Mike. But of course any game Bryan Sanders plays as QB you have a chance to pull out a win. Everyone hates Bryan Sanders so much. Bryan Sanders you are the Roger from Sister Sister of the DCGFFL. Stop ruining everyone’s Sundays and go home Bryan. The game started off as it should have with new QB RJ at the helm.  RJ then realized his elbow had a boo boo and Bryan Sanders stole the football and weaseled his way into another victory he didn’t deserve.  The first half had two scores and no conversions, for Power Blue, Greg Carter – for Forest Green, RJ.  In the second half Joe Heron made a valiant effort to keep Bryan out of the spotlight, but when the game was on the line Bryan physically wrestled the ball away from Joe and won the game down the stretch with a tie breaking pass to Jason. Andrew E. helped jack the win from the Power Blue C*** Monsters with three game saving sacks.  All hail Queen Bryan. May he never lose again?
results_3_description: These inexplicably French Dolphins (I guess French is more ‘royal’ than English) hit all their jumps and entered Season XIII with a splash!  Hot & Gold ended up more Gold than Hot this week. One of the highest billed games of the week lived up to expectations with an Overtime Extravaganza. The first half was a standard affair with QB AJ and Captain Levert of the French Dolphins rushing, throwing, catching, intercepting and topping their way to a 7 point lead and not sharing the ball at all with their teammates. Gold saw a bit more diversity with scores to Antoine and James Davis and a conversion to AJ along with an interception by Will. After scores from Gold’s Sheerod, AJ & James D. with a 2 pt conversion from Will J. and two scores from Zgoda and a try from Richard, things were all tied at 33. Gold went first scoring on their first overtime attempt and converting their measly one point conversion.  The kings and queens of the ocean answered back immediately and aggressively with a score of their own and a whopping TWO point conversion. Both of these teams proved to be contenders this week, but the bucket of fish goes to Les Dauphins this week.
results_4_description: PBR shot the ball and walked away before seeing if they made it.  The ball rimmed out or Chris Morse goal tended depending on who you ask. The first half was all PBR combining for three interceptions between John Boyd (2) and Kozak (1) along with scores from Sima and Chris G. Charcoal had a decent defensive effort with a sack from Sean Stern and two ints by Dan Honberg one on what would turn out to be a game deciding conversion try. The Charholes left a bad taste in the Rimmers mouth when they stormed back in the second half to take the lead 13 -12 off of touchdowns from Cam, Adam, and a one point try from Chris M. PBR took a wet nap to the holes and climbed back ahead to take an 18-13 lead but AGAIN couldn’t connect on the conversion. Charcoal rolled down the field with another TD to Cam and put an exclamation point on the win with an interception by Dan H.  Final score 19-18 Charholes.
results_5_description: Face down, ass up that’s the way we like to lose. The Lumbers Jacked all over their competition in the second half to earn Bryan Sanders yet another win that will be vacated three years from now because of cheating. In the first half it was all Ashy with scores to BB (2), James R. (1) and trys to Scott G (1), and Jamar (1). Forest had TD’s from CJ and Tyler S. with an added try from Jason W. bringing the score to 20-13. Ash to Mouth didn’t bring their face up enough to breath in the second only managing one sack by Seaton. The Lumber Jackers pulled ahead and never looked back to see whose face was in their crack. CJ racked up another touchdown and two ints, Kyle M. had two scores, and Andrew E. had an int. Go home Bryan Sanders.
results_6_description: Both teams played earlier, both teams lost.  One had to come away with a win.  Cookie Monsters came out with a strong first half. TJ B. had two touchdowns, Jeremy S. had a touchdown and a sack, Rudy and Greg C. both had interceptions and Shara grabbed a conversion to give the Monsters a 19-7 lead at half.  Orange’s Jared (td) and Randy (1 pt. try) tried their best to keep pace, but it wasn’t aca-enough. The second half the Peaches tried to starve out the monsters with fresh fruit, but it didn’t come to fruitition. Peach Perfect’s Patrick M’s sack, Nick’s td, and Greg C.’s Td and 2 point conversion weren’t enough to overcome Rudy’s touchdown and second interception and Greg C’s touchdown from Commissioner QB Gurg Kinterdean.
results_7_description: The Black Plague edged Sexual Chocolate all morning until they finished victorious and tired. I feel like every team name is an AIM SN from my 2004 AAU Basketball Team. This game can be summarized with four words. Jordan, Jordan, Jordan, Staci! Brown tried their hardest to win this game but clock management got the best of them and they ended up giving All-American Running Back Jordan Anderson a chance to get his team back in the game with under two minutes left. Brown's Sean K. had an interception and the go ahead touchdown in the second half, while Cammas ran for the first Td and Kostyk had both one point conversions.  But the Black Plague had given Sexual Chocolate a fever and the only cure was STACI PUGH. She came up huge and gutsy with a 2 point conversion after a come from behind touchdown from Jordan Anderson.
results_8_description: Midnight drew first blood but turned into pumpkins soon thereafter. Kelly won. By a bunch. Maybe more than a bunch. Midnight didn't have their qb and it was over by halftime. Adam flag guarded once threw two interceptions to Alex P. and Santos. Santos and MopTop scored a couple times but it didn’t matter because Adam also threw six touchdowns to Taylor S (3), Brett Chambers(2), and Kahlil F.(1). Kelly also racked up 5 ints from Brett(2), Andrew, Matt T., and Kahlil. Brent had a sack too. Final score was 37-19.
results_9_description: Maroon 5 Uncut was cut from the undefeated list early this year with their loss to the winner for the grossest name in a year full of gross names, Blumpkin Spice. Neither of you deserve a recap based on your terrible names so here are stat lines: Evan Binder had an interception return for 2 points, Austin Plier had three touchdown catches and an interception, Matt Nix had a point conversion and Brandon Waggoner surprisingly rushed for a touchdown. Blumpkins sat atop their throne of poop and blew away the completion touchdowns to Sean Gard, Barry Mauck (2), and Donald Hughes (2). Sean Gard added a sack and Max R. added an int. Tim Adams scored a conversion.  Final score 32-27.
results_10_description: When a scorecard only has Andy Allen on it, you know it was a rough game. Andy had two touchdowns and an interception and that’s literally all Power Yellow was able to mustard. This cream pie slipped on a banana peel on their way to the field. Ash dominated this game from beginning to end. Scott Graham of all people had an interception to start off the game. James R, BB and Jamar(3) all had touchdowns. James added a second int and JC a sack to these. Power Yellow landed face first in their own Banana Cream Pies.
results_11_description: Kellyfornication was high off of their first win of the season as they took the field for their double header matchup with Sky Curious. Kelly’s QB, Adam Martin, came out red hot with a touchdown on his first pass of the game! Unfortunately for Adam and Kelly the touchdown was to Baby Blue’s rookie Chris Ralphs. This theme would continue for most of the game. Baby Blue’s Defense and ‘straight’ QB Jack Blaney took control from that moment on. After the opening pick six the first half saw two touchdowns and a two point conversion to Chris Rybicki, a rushing touchdown by Jack B., a couple sacks by captain Tom Loughran, another touchdown to Chris Ralphs and a fifth touchdown and second int to OJ. Kelly Green got one first down to Brett Chambers. In the second half Kelly rallied and pulled up even with Sky Curious, in the parking lot on the way out of Carter Baron, since the game ended so early with a Mercy Rule. Final score was a bloated 54-6 with added scores from William Lipovsky, Chris Rybicki and Jason Clevenger on Baby Blue and a cute deep bomb garbage touchdown from Adam to Kevin Z for Kelly. David Duchovny was never railed this hard.
results_12_description: A low scoring game turned into something of a blow out when Fuschia was bested by Vegas Gold 19-6.  The first half saw the game tied at 6 all with scores by Fuschialicious Jerrell P, and Vegas Gold Knight’s Captain Dameron. TBH I can’t read this score card but it looks like Vegas had a great second half. Sam Smallwood did something, so did Ken Gaughan and Dameron did something else.  So did Sean and Andy. Final Score 19-6 Vegas Gold wins.

results_1_description: Teal: DMitch (TD x3, XP1), Cammas (TD x2, XP1, INT);  Forest: Payne (TD), Yuan (TD x2), Combs (TD), Nolan (XP1)
results_2_description: Black: Harvey (TD, XP1), Dewayne (TD x2, XP1, INT), DeGarmo (INT), Scott Graham (TD), Dameron (Pick6), Veldman (XP1);  Neon Green: Rothschild (TD, XP1), Plier (TD, Pick6, INT)
results_3_description: Graphite: Colt (TD, XP1), Pearce (INT), BJ (TD); Purple:  Reust (TD, Pick6, XP1, XP2), Jordan (TD x4, Pick6), Lipovsky (XP2), Hess (INT)
results_4_description: Maroon: Jared (TD x2, XP1, INT), Erkenbrack (TD), Luis (XP2), Zajac (TD x2, XP1), Earl (TD); Kelly: Carter (TD x2, XP1, XP2), Javi (TD), Jucha (TD)
results_8_mvp: John Clemons (Sky Blue), Evan Binder (Neon Yellow)
results_5_description: Orange: Karson (TD x2, XP1), Burrell (TD), Isaac (INT); Olive: Smiffy (TD x2, Sack), Jack (TD x2, XP1, INT), Banwo (Sack x2),  Waggoner (INT x2)
results_6_description: Royal: OJ (TD x2), Nix (XP2); Silver: Kozak (Sack), Gillyard (TD), BLong (XP1)
results_7_description: Navy: KDan (Sack), Brad (TD x3, XP1), Marcus (Sack x2), Strasberg (TD, INT), Bobby (TD); White: Hofberg (TD x3), Larry (Sack), Mezetin (Sack)

results_0_description: Graphite, down two reliable receivers, counted on Jim Roll and BJ Bundy to lead their offense. They both scored touchdowns; Sean Stern scored two extra points. But it wasn’t enough to overcome Marvin’s two running touchdowns and Marlon’s through the air, handing reigning-championship quarterback Matt Pearce his second loss of the season.
results_1_description: George Garner, filling in Earl Armstrong’s pocket, connected with Brian Golden, Billy Lechert, and Mike ZGoda for scores in Maroon’s win. Neyoncé’s Captain Alonzo and Andy Merterns did their best to spoil the backup’s Season XII debut, picking off Garner three times. But their touchdowns, Max Rothschild’s pair, and Dan Cipullo’s fell short.
results_2_description: Teal eeked out a win over Silver behind Drew Halunen’s two touchdowns and scores from Bryant and Brett. Cammas and Kenderdine claimed three extra points.  Kozak snagged two touchdowns in the loss, including one acrobatic end zone grab.
results_3_description: Sky’s Sherrod got back to his winning ways, finding Matt Gander and Rob Casey twice for touchdowns and Adam Robbins in Kelly’s backfield for a sack. Alpha’s day belonged to Greg Carter, who hauled in two scores, two extra points, and an interception. He was not to be outdone by Matt Peseskey, who added a touchdown and a sack of his own.
results_4_description: The high winds didn't keep these two potent offenses from filling up the stat sheet. Eveuntally Red prevailed with a one score lead as White ran out of gas without their Queen Bee Captian Larry Womack. Brian Sparrow sliced and diced all day with his numerous weapons, leading the well oiled offense against a (usually) tough Mark Hoffberg-led defense. Michele Ta-a scored two TD's and a PAT. and Brandon Benjamin had a whopping 4 TD's for Red! These two teams are now in the middle of the pack in their division, let's see who rises to the top in this second half of the season!
results_5_description: Royal: OJ 4 TDs, Nix 1 TD, Nick & Jeremy 1XP each.  INT by OJ and Sacks by Jeremy and Charlie.  Gold: Clay 1 Sack; Neiswanger 1 INT & 1 TD;  Ryan Boyle 1 TD
results_6_description: Boaty Call received in the first half, and The Mangerines could do little to stop them.  On the first drive, Bryan Sanders found Will Chappell in the end zone (followed up by an XP1 by Baxter O’Brien).  After an interception by Adam Strasberg, Aaron Ross scored a TD (but the XP attempt was stopped by an interception by Ren McKinnon) to put the score at 13-0.  The Mangerines finally pulled it together in the second drive, with Ren throwing to Sean Karson for Orange’s first TD, but Navy’s Chappell responded with another TD.  With the clock running low in the first half, Ren found Sam Brown twice for a TD and XP1 to end the half 19-13 (Navy).  However, Orange lost its focus in the second half and could not stop Navy.  Strasberg, Chappell, and O’Brien each had 1 TD.  Chappell had 2 XP1s and Baxter had an INT.
results_7_description: Neon Yellow, still glowing from the Spring Break sun, shone brighter than Sand all day Sunday. In the first half, Tyler hit three different receivers for scores -- Binder, Andy Larson, and Diggy -- before running in one himself. Sandstorm only rustled up one, a lob from Long to MopTop nearing halftime. On defense, Larson and Diggy grabbed an interception each.  Hotchkiss and Austan "M" notched sacks. In the second, Foxy lit up the scoreboard with two unanswered touchdowns to Rudy and Binder before adding another on the ground. Andy Allen's late interception and touchdown, plus Eduardo's sixty-yard bomb weren't enough to brighten Sand's day.
results_8_description: In a battle of the (darker) Greens, Forest took undefeated Olive down to the very last drive. Alex Pane looked impressive filling in for QB Matt Cline as he was smart and methodical against a big Olive Defense. It helped to have YAC speedsters like Howard Yuan and Keith Combs, who had the Martinis stirring all game long. Eventually, some mistakes cost Forest the win as they lost by just one point. Olive is the hottest team in the first half of the season, but QB Brandon Waggoner knows what dominance looks like and this wasn't it!
results_9_description: Joe Heron earned his first career touchdown in Gold’s loss to Navy. Captain Clay Arnold added their only other score on the day: An early-series collision between teammates Andrew Carr and Craig Neiswanger knocked the wind from their and their team’s sails. For Navy, Will Coachman hauled in two scores from Bryan Sanders. Brad Allen and Baxter O’Brien pulled interceptions; Aaron Ross, an extra point.
results_10_description: Riding high after their 32-12 win over Gold, BATTLE ROYALE expected little opposition from the 0-4 Mangerines, but Orange wasn’t ready to yield.  Charlie Salem scored Royal’s first TD, but Orange stopped the XP attempt and responded with a TD of their own by Sean Karson.  Jim ran down the clock and gave the TD and XP1 to Jeremy Steslicki, leaving little time for Orange to respond and ending the half at 13-6.  In the second half, however, Royal destroyed Orange’s defense, putting up 2 more TDs (by Jim and OJ) and an XP (by Charlie) before Orange rallied.  Ren found supplemental pick Lindsey Walton, about whom Royal’s sidelines warned but against whom Royal’s defense could do nothing.  Karson stopped Royal’s next drive with an INT, allowing Isaac Voehringer to score the TD and XP1 to bring the score to 26-19.  With less than 2 minutes in the game, Levert James stepped in as primary rush, blocking and intercepting a pass by Connolly and giving Orange a chance to tie or win the game.  Karson scored on the 2nd of 3 plays to bring the score 26-25 (Royal).  Orange went for the win instead of overtime, but Ren McKinnon was downed 2 yards shy of the end zone, giving Orange their fifth loss of the season.
results_11_description: Jordan Anderson, Joe Green, Mike Hess, and Cody Barry scored touchdowns in Purple’s romp. Kyle Veldman and Andy Pratt mustered Black’s two scoes. Derrick Johnson continued to pile up sacks, adding another to his League-leading season total.

results_0_description: Daylight proved hard Sky to find on Sunday: Blue only managed a sack by Mecha S in the first half. Jens P serving as QB briefly peaked out from behind the clouds in the second. He found Chris R and Matt G for TDs. But the sandstorm proved to be too much for him to see through. QB Long D not only ran in a TD, he threw TD passes Brendan M and Jason R. Brendan M also had an XP along with Chris L. Sean H added an INT while Eduardo C had a sack.
results_2_description: The seafaring Boaties navigated dutifully through the Forest on Sunday. Green’s Nolan L and Alex P each had TDs and Keith C added an XP, Barry M helped with a sack. Alas, the Woods weren’t tall enough to stop the Boaties as Bryan S found Will C for 3 TDs. He also found Gabe A. for 1 TD, and Aaron R., Brad A., and Baxter O. for XPs. He and Will C. also grabbed INTs.
results_3_description: 5 minutes before kick-off, Royal only had 5 palyers and both teams were already thinking about getting out of the cold and going to brunch. Then in the distance Matt Fransien was seen racing towards Carter Barron and Royal had just enough to play (six), albiet with a less than 100% Jeremey Steslicki who was making an early return from last years knee injury. He must have had the same doctors as Adrian Peterson because Jeremey did not skip a beat. With every catch, dive, and slip in the mud spectators watched in awe (and a little bit of fear). The Slaytroopers were thinking about the mimosas a little too soon becuase before they knew it, Royal was leading at halftime! Both offenses were clicking as it turned into a classic shoot out of smart short-game and home-run football. At the end of the day White knew what they had to do if they wanted to win the game, and that was stop the trainwreck! Late in the game, Mark Hofberg came up with a huge interception then drive to take take the lead and then newcomer Jen Jones sealed the win with a game ending interception of her own!
results_5_description: Billy K’s shook and stirred House TargaryRed in Season XII debut, scoring 2 XPs, nabbing 1 INT and 1 TD. While Smiffy had a TD and an 2 INTs, and Jack M had one INT. Stu S and Brandon W both had TDs as well. Captain Porter S. and his House -- of the mightiest winos in Westeros -- couldn’t handle their the strength of Olive’s martinis. They only managed TDs by Christian S and Sam C. and two sacks by Tom L.
results_6_description: AKA’s Illustrious ladies’ showed off their finest in Sunday’s mixer with Jam It In’s gentlemen. Kelly’s QB, Adam R, grabbed INT from Purple’s Adam M. Captain Josh E scored an early a TD, but Coach G was the star of this show with 3 TDs and an XP.  Impressive as Kelly looked, Purple stole the show. Jordan A had an impressive game with 3 INTs, 2TDs and an XP. Will L added a TD and XP. While Mike H had a TD and AJ found the end zone for and XP. Adam M made it look easy as he not only threw those TD passes but he ran in for 3 TDs of his own.
results_7_description: The Barbies welcomed to Maroon to their Dream House for brunch on Sunday. Gracious hosts, they were not. Marvin W not only had an INT but also scored 2 TD and an XP while finding Jamar W for three TDs and an XP, while Sam S had a TD. Andrew E. added an INT. Maroon was only offered one TD by Chris M, an INT by Earl A., and a mimosa that was mostly orange juice.
results_8_description: Orange hoped for a win after last week’s shutout from Gold, but they weren’t successful even with their primary QB, Ren McKinnon, back from the disabled list.  Teal kicked off to start the game, but Orange missed catches and turned over the ball on downs in their own territory.  Teal’s Drew Halunen scored shortly after and was backed up by an extra point from Bryan Burnheimer.  Orange’s second drive was stopped short when Bill Cammas intercepted a bounce-off after Sam Brown failed to catch the football with his face.  For the rest of the half, Orange’s receivers could not catch nor could their defense stop Burnheimer (x2) and Brett Chambers from scoring TDs.  Donald Mitchell and Cammas punched in extra points to make the score 27-0 at the half.  In the second half, Orange finally started to click.  Ren spread the ball around to Dave Davis, Isaac Voehringer, Sean Karson, Peter Gately, Brown, and Levert James (who scored both of Orange’s TDs). Meanwhile, Orange’s defense made Teal work hard to move the ball down the field and held them to 2 TDs (by Bill and Donald).  Overall, Orange showed promise in the second half, but Teal’s experience and discipline dominated the first 30 minutes of the game.
results_9_description: The Silverstones left the scoreboard shining in their first game on Sunday. Unfortunately their luster wore off the second of their doubleheader. After hanging 40 on Gold, Silver could only muster 1 Joe C  TD against Olive. Brian added 1 INT and Kozak and Joe C each had sacks. Making a stunning entrance to the Dirty Martini’s Cocktail Party, Billy K. wowed with 2 INTs, 2 TDs, and a dazzling designer knee-brace. Stu S added 3 TDs. Captain Kevin S. and Jack each added XPs.
results_10_description: Adam M tried to jam it in again in the second game of Purple’s double header. He stuck TD passes to the hands of AJ, Mike, Will L, and Jordan A. Mike H and AJ both had INTs as well and AJ had an XP. Earl A., too slippery for Jam, led Maroon though in their second game of the day. TD passes to Mike Z (3), Billy L, and Chris M and INT’s by Jason B and Earl A sealed the win for Maroona Matata.
results_11_description: Colt S. did a great job filling in as QB for Graphite, connecting with Kevin K. (2), Alex H., and B.J for touchdowns. Alex, BJ and Sean S. grabbed extra points. Colt also helped his cause on defense, nabbing an INT. Neon Green, fielding its full roster with regular QB, Dan C., played at full strength. Dan threw TDs to Josh R, Max R (3) and Michelle F. While Austin P caught two XPs to hand graphite their first loss of the season. Alonzo M. had a sack in the win.

results_0_description: Bryan S called this navy boat to attention with their first TD of the day with Will C following up with the XP.  Gabe A added a TD later in the first half. Alicia thought she struck pay dirt with a TD to Joe C  but Navy man Baxter O had an INT on the point after attempt and pay dirt turned into just dirt as these Silver stones could not dig up another score the rest of the day. Navy meanwhile came ashore with with two more TDs in the second half, one by Will C and one by Baxter O. Bobby B added an XP after that one.  Adam S. wanted to add an INT to close out the game. David P was one of three players in the DCGFFL to have three sacks in their game this week.
results_1_description: Sand took the first half by storm with an amazing performance by Andy A who had two TD’s. While purple wasn’t jamin at all and could only muster a couple of sacks by Joe G. However the sand sank quick in the second half and were blanked by a purple team who was finally jell-n with a TD and XP by Will L. AJ added an INT so that Jordan could score the first of two TDs for the day. Jordan also added in and INT after Joe G added his third sack for the day and Will L added two other XPs after his D1 players took over the game.  Mike H would also like to add that “I had in INT in the game as well”
results_2_description: Maroona Matata seemed to get lost in the jungle of Graphite Content. Graphite QB gave a Warning to “Catch the….ball” to his teammates and Jim R payed attention and started the scoring with a TD. Kevin K who usually doesn’t listen to any warnings must have been paying attention because he then scored a TD of his own. Captain Sean S was so intent to follow his QB’s warning he caught the ball from the other teams QB for an INT. Matt P decided to run in the next two TDs for Graphite to end the half. They only added one more TD to Jim R but they really didn’t need it. Maroon QB Earl A got the lion share of the maroon’s stats with their only TD in the first half and an INT in the second half even though he was sacked by graphite rusher John B. George G did get on the stat sheet for maroon with a TD but it wasn’t enough to win against his former captain.
results_3_mvp: Josh R. (Neon Green); Brian H. (Neon Yellow)
results_3_game-ball: Christine H. (Neon Green); Will J. (Neon Yellow)
results_3_description: In the battle of the Neons it was the Yellow who was glowing brighter and got the job done. One of QB Tyler F’s favorite targets Will J opened the scoring with a TD for the glow jobs. Andy L who took off week one said don’t forget about me Tyler I was on your team last season too and was promptly rewarded with a TD of his own.  I’m the captain here so I’ll take the 2XP thank you very much, said Mike D. Tyler added and INT so he could find Mike D for his own TD and let Will add the 2XP this time.  Tyler opened the second half with another INT so Brian H could not only get a TD for himself but add his own 2XP and even added a sack. Evan B thought he should be on the stat sheet too so he added his own sack and Will said enough of this and added another TD for good measure. Neyonce’ tried to start the game off right with a TD from Dan C to captain ZO with an additional XP by Michelle F but could only manage one more TD to Josh R the rest of the first half.  Neyonce’ did a little better in the second half with a TD from sliver fox Brain D and another TD by Austin P with Brian D adding 2XP wasn’t enough to dance away with a win.
results_4_description: I don’t think Gold had fun last week but this week they surely did on their way to a win over the mangerines. QB Meredith B took over after Andrew C gave her the ball by getting and INT on the mangerines first possession. She quickly rewarded Andrew by hitting him for Golds first TD of the season. Craig N secured the XP and Gold was on the way to a fun day. Orange couldn’t get much going on offense and Craig N intercepted a pass to give the ball back to Gold. Meredith threw Andrew another TD. Then a nice toss to Clay A. to add the XP.  Craig N opened the second half with a TD and Ryan B added an XP. Jason C. who could possibly be the reason for the turn-around added his own TD. Craig added his second INT and Bihn L added two sacks on the mangerines replacement QB.  Jason found his way to the end zone for his second TD with Rachel B adding the XP.
results_7_mvp: Marvin W. (Power Blue); John C. (Sky Blue)
results_5_description: The Slaytroopers navigated through the forest in a toe-to-toe game. Mark Hofberg was all over the place again with 4 TD's, 1 rush TD, 3 rush PAT's, and a whopping 5 picks on defense! That got white out of the Morning Woods which had TD's from 3 different players and big rush all-day with Ricky.
results_6_description: Congratulations on your first DCGFFL TD Keaton F. You accounted for all the scoring for your team in the first half. Unfortunately, the coin toss for this game came up teal. They had first half TD scores by Bill C and D-Mitch. While Bryant B added an INT and Sequoia H and Drew H (no relation) each added a sack. Teal went into half time with a 6 point lead. With BB adding a TD and Porter B and James B (again no relation) each added a sack, Red looked to slay their opponent in this close game. Someone must have used a two teals coin. Much like the first half teal did just enough to keep the game in their favor. Bryant B scored a second half TD for teal while Greg K added the XP that turned out to be the deciding point. Red tried to claw their way back into the game with a TD score by Sam C. However those elusive XPs let teal slay the dragon as D-Mitch came up with an INT to seal the win.
results_7_game-ball: Alex A. (Power Blue);  Matt G. (Sky Blue)
results_7_description: The Power was up in the Sky with this game as the two blues battled back and forth for most of the game. The Handsome Ken doll on the barbies, Nick B, helped get them on the scoreboard with his first DCGFFL TD with an XP by the old soldier Marlon D. Marvin W wanted the ball back on offense so he decided to get an INT while on defense so he could find the other old soldier Sam S. for a TD.  While Alex A added a sack and Marlon D thought he should get his own INT.  Marvin W scored his own TD in the second half and then tossed another one to Marlon D….Soldier on.  As much as sky tried stay in touch with the power in the first have with a TD by John C and XP by Matt G.  and a sack by James D. they even tried to keep up into the second half with Sheerod W scoring a TD and XP and then finding John C again for a TD and Matt G again for the XP their back finally went out and couldn’t keep the power.
results_8_description: It might be too early to knight this royal player “Sir OJ” but he scored in impressive fashion with three TDs, two on long bombs and one weaving through the defense. Two of which in the first half and one in the second half along with a second half XP. One who truly deserves the title of “Sir Charlie” (he has an award named after him after all) also scored in the second half for Royal. But this Battle tested team couldn’t hold their alcohol, at least not Martini’s.This was the perfect Olive for the drink as QB Brandon W worked with another HOFer Tony S for a TD and two XP’s, one in each half. Smiffy had two TDs and an INT in the first half and added an INT in the second half. Jack M had his own INT in the first half. QB Brandon W ran in a TD of his own late in the second half.
results_9_description: This game was a coin toss and it at the end of the long slay, it landed on Teals. In a game featuring two of the most athletic QB's in the league, Bill C came out on top by spreading the wealth with 5TD's to 4 different recievers. A young scrappy and hungry Captian Larry Womack did his best with 2TD's and 1 INT, but the troopers came up just one "pew-pew" too short. It came down to the last play... with White on their heels, Teal sealed the deal despite an Appeal. Fo' Real.
results_10_description: The Dragon of House Targary-Red had obviously never experienced morning wood before and it was stuck in the forest all day. With  Ryan getting a sack in the first half and Porter B, Lynnette C (with her first in the DCGFFL) and Sam C all scoring TDs. Then BB scoring a TD in the second half didn’t help them fight through the trees. The Woods were too thick, with scoring. Two First half TDs by the biggest wood Nolan L. who added a third in the second half. Wood captain Howard scored an XP in the first half and a TD in the second while Ricky J had a sack in the first half. Kieth C had a TD in the second half while Alex P had and INT and Barry M had a sack while playing with his wood.
results_11_description: Alpha Kelly Alpha struggled in the first half with only one TD by QB Adam R. Luckily Black couldn’t get that ass into the end zone more than once themselves with a TD by Andy P but they did get their XP by Scott G (heal up buddy, rest the ankle). Sadly the Justin P was the only ass that could back up into the end zone in the second half. Derrick J worked his ass off today though adding three more sacks to his total after he was challenged by someone who said he might not be the best rusher in the league. While the corporation worked the whole game and in the second half they had Greg C who is slowly making a name for himself in the DCGFFL with two TDs and an INT. Already well known Coach G scored a TD as well. Adam R scored and XP and Bobby H scored a TD as well while Braden B added two sacks of his own.

@graph.description: Washington D.C. Gay Flag Football League

results_0_description: AKA Inc. took charge, dismembering Barbies limb from limb. For Kelly, Adam R. dominated, running in a TD (and XP) of his own he threw a TD to Daniel H. and Javi D. Newcomer Greg C impressed in his debut, catching 2 TDs an XP and had an INT. Matt P might have been a little rusty in week one as he only had one sack. Brain J also added and extra point. Marvin W. was plastic fantastic for the Barbies, hitting Sam S. and Marlon D. for one touchdown each and Jamar W. for two.
results_1_description: Just when you think you’re out somehow you get pulled back in, isn’t that right Brian S. who came back to QB House Targary-Red and the dragon certainly breathed fire all over the mangerines. Isaac V scored his first DCGFFL TD on a pass from new QB Ren M. who promptly hit center Dave D, who returns to the DCGFFL from a few season on hiatus, for the XP but that’s all the offense they could manage for the first half. While House Targary-Red had TD’s from BB and the Sparrow himself. Keaton F added a sack to his resume’ going back to last season. Red seemed to be on control of the game with second half TDs by Sam C. and BB. Ken G kept the mangerines at bay with an INT but eventually the  Mangerines offense tried to peel the scales off the Red dragon with a sack by head Mangerine Levert and then Cameron B finally showed  up on the stat sheet after he turned a short pass from backup QB Levert into an 80 yard TD. Red captain Porter B, not to be out done pulled off a nice 80 yrd TD run of his own after a short pass from Brian S. However Cameron B didn’t like that and decided to intercept reds xp attempt and run it back to give the mangerines the two points. Isaac V added a second TD and an INT as he and Cam helped pull the mangerines closer by adding his second TD of the day. With Red only leading by one point and Orange looking to steal the win Brain S kept Red in the lead with a pick 6.
results_2_description: It was a close game between Olive and Navy, with teams scoring back and forth in both halves. Smiffy led Olive to three touchdowns in the first, accompanied by a fourth from handsome Jack. Tony added an extra point and Stu had an awesome interception. The first half for Navy saw two TDs from Brad, an extra point from Randy, a sack from Strasberg and an interception and extra point from Sanders. The second half for Olive saw a TD from Tony (I’ll get it on camera next time!) and a TD and extra point from Jack, as well as Brandon’s second-ever sack.  Navy’s second half had a TD from Sanders and two TDs from Marcus (congrats!), interceptions by Brad and Baxter, and extra points from Sanders and Baxter.
results_3_description: In a back and forth game, offenses were on a roll and points flowed like wine.  For the victorious Royal team, OJ led with 3 TD's and an XP, Matt Nix had 2 and Nick Christiansen added the other.  Extra points matter - and Scott Williams had 2 which ended up being the difference over Teal.  The difference in the game was an INT by OJ in the 2nd half.  Teal scored on all their other drives.  2 TD's each for Bryant Burnheimer and Brett Chambers.  Bill Cammas ran in a TD and Greg Kenderdine also caught a score.  Down by 1 with time expired, Teal elected to go for 2 and the victory as opposed to sending the game to overtime.  The final attempt was intercepted by Matt Nix and Jim Connolly ends his regular season losing streak in dramatic fashion.
results_4_description: Neyonce’ took over this game like their namesake took over a recent half time show. Max R tried to pick up where he left off last season and scored two TD’s in the first half each time ZO added the XP after. Austin P didn’t want to be left out so he scored a TD in the first half as well. Josh R and Tim A each had a sack. Josh wanted more than just a sack so he added an INT in the second half as well as a second sack later in the game. Austin P said I want more too and added another TD while Dan C added the XP and said I like this so he added another XP after he threw a TD to Brian D.  Purple tried to Jam It In as much as they could, Will L had a TD and INT in the first half and DCGFFL newbie Jordan A added his first TD. But that jam wasn’t going to spread too much in the second half as Adam ran in a TD and Jordan A added his second TD. Tough loss but really not a bad way to start your DCGFFL career.
results_5_description: Graphite took the early lead in the first half with a score by QB Matt P followed by a stop and a score by Graphite's Jim R.  Sand caught their footing, and came back to exchange scores with MopTop and Butterworth scoring for Sand and Jayme scoring for Graphite.  Graphite warned Sand at the halftime whistle they had a change in strategy coming. But Sand chose not to isten, keeping their head in the sand.  The stellar rush of Bryan J, Rob W and John B took over the game, overwhelmed the Sand QB and offensive line, tallying 2 sacks in the process; resulting in a second half shut out.  Graphite scored 2 TDs in the half, 1 more each for Matt P and Jim R.  A tale of two halves, a 1 score game at halftime turned into a 32-13 victory for Graphite.
results_6_description: Derrick J helped black that a** up and blue that back out of the sky with 5 sacks in his first half of his first game of the day. I don’t think Sheerod has ever been sacked that many times in a game let alone a half but he did manage to hit John C for a TD. Blacks offense was only able to muster one TD by Andy P in the first half as well. Blacks offense wasn’t much better in the second half, again only getting one TD by Dameron but this time Andy ran in his XP. Sky blues back issues must have been getting better as the game went on because they managed to have two players with ½ a sack each (James D and Paige W- how you get half a sack ill never know) and then Sheerod overcame the rush and managed to find John C again for a TD and this time he hit Rob C for a 2XP that won the game.
results_7_description: Forest started off on Defense but that didn’t stop Barry M from trying to get on the stat sheet early. On Golds first drive Barry had an INT and gave the ball to the Morning Wood offense where Matt C started his stat sheet tally by hitting Howard for the games first TD. Matt didn’t want to stop playing offense so he picked off Gold again and Gold had no answer for Matts offensive attack He continued to rack up stats throughout the game with 5 more TD passes to Jason T., Alex P., Barry M.,  Lane M., and Nolan L. Matt C added XP passes to Nolan L., Jason T., and Barry M. Matt Finished off his day with a second INT. Matts only mis-step was giving up a sack to Golds Binh L.
results_8_description: Chris M’s Maroon Matata and Mike D’s Glow Jobs trade blows and scores tic for tat on Sunday. Neon Yellow struck first with the opening half only score, a short distance score from Tyler F to Captain Mike D. After a half of long, methodical drives to shake off an offseason of rust, both teams came out punching in the second half. Brian G snagged a pair of spectacular catches on Maroon’s opening drive including a touchdown. Chris Morse added another. But Will J and Kip M hauled in long strikes from Tyler F to pull the Glow Jobs ahead. Sacks from Evan B and Mike D on Maroon’s final drive sealed the game for Neon Yellow. Round One: Glow Jobs.
results_9_description: The Sandstorm overcame a tough loss in their first game to win the second game of their doubleheader. Rookie Chris B added to his game one stats by pulling in his second TD of the day while Sam B added the XP. Andy A caught a TD and Chris B added the XP. The second half started with Miles adding a TD Andy A added his second TD and MopTop had a TD between two INTs. Although Black had the lead at half time with Dameron catching two TDs and an XP along with TDs to new girl (and yes its girl not gurl) Alex H. and dirty gurl Justin P. They could only black that a** up one more time with a TD to Dameron in the second half, losing their second close game of the day. Derrick J had 3 more sacks on the day for black bringing his daily yes daily total to 8, what kind of season is he going to have!
results_10_description: The season's first matchup of undefeated teams began with 3 straight scores from Graphite with TDs from veterans BJ B and Sean S and one from rookie Colt S.  The defense was bolstered again by a strong rush from Rob W and Bryan J.  Sky QB Sheerod W cut the lead to 2 scores with an impressive run in the redzone as the half neared an end.  Graphite got the ball back with less than 2 minutes to go and put together a drive that was nearly derailed with a sack from Sky's rookie Paige.  Last play heroics from Matt P and an amazing catch from Jayme F to end the half.  Sky and Graphite exchanged TD's throughout the second half. Then, the physical toll of a Week 1 doubleheader set in.  Jim R, BJ B and Colt added TD's to Graphite's total along with an XP from Alex H and two more sacks for Rob W.  Sky added another running TD from Sheerod W and a TD from Rob C along with 2 XPs.
results_11_description: Ken Gaugan’s totally rad socks and Haskell N’s impressive impressive rookie quarterbacking debut weren’t enough for the Silverstones on Sunday. Despite leading White at the half, the Silverstones came up short against veteran QB Mark Hofberg and a team effort by the shorthanded SlayTroopers. Impressive on both ends considering that both QB's had just gotten off a plane from overseas!   Joe Cappola filled the stat sheet with a TD, PAT, and an INT for Silver and Captain Kozak did his best facial expressions (check out the photo gallery!) because anything you can do to draw attention to your mouth (not fist) is good. The force was with White the second half as they settled into their formation with TD's from Mark, Steve Gong and Justin Mezetin and two game changing picks from Justin and Mark. Are there questions of Silver turning their mosaic into a finely detailed work of art this season? As-if! Of course they will, the night is young!

results_0_comment: In a battle of 4-1 teams, this Friday Night Light's game looked to be a doozy, but it was not meant to be. The Commissioner poured over these two team names for several hours trying to understand what both of them meant to try to be funny and cheeky.  Urban Dictionary?? No thank you. Matt Pearce and gang came out rolling without their captain and put on the gas with three TDs to Joe Cappola and two more to Max Rothschild.  Without BB and Brian Donohoe there to help him out, Gerard struggled to get into a groove, other than re-injuring newbie Kostyk to the team and bidding him Adieu.  Derrick Johnson was the sole shining start for the Trap Greens with a couple of sacks and their lone TD.
results_1_comment: In just the third time in league history, a team forfeitted a game due to a shortage of players.  Mercy Rule it is!  Hotchkiss has been known to have Friday Night magic before.  Did he miss his best shot at victory this season?
results_2_comment: This game seemed to set the tone for a day of hard-fought games. This game rallied back-n-forth with O and D and rushing and interceptions all playing a role in this good match. Silver Captain DMitch was QB Dan C’s love—and target--for the day. Dan had DMitch running routes all over the field and particularly effective along the sideline. Teal’s D struggled to make the proper adjustments as veteran Dan changed up his plays. DMitch rallied his team to the endzone with a TD and XP to follow. But Dan’s new valentine, Drew H, found lots of love of his own. Solid catches and rushing yards helped The Silver Situation. Drew H brought home a TD. Silver’s Mike O followed with one of his own. Teal QB Bryan S shrugged. He met Aaron R for a TD and an XP. Tealor Alonzo M snagged an INT. “That, my friends, is why I’m on a travel team. Now watch me twerq.” At the half, Silver was leading this match. Teal came back with new focus and drag queen authority as Captain Mike Z guided his troops to a stronger second half. “Gurl, use your hips and your legs. Like me.” Taking heed, QB Bryan S started dancing down the field by way of a smart pitch game stacking up yards like Z’s wigs. Good field placement gave Bryan the opportunity to dominant the O for his team. He scored twice, added an XP and connected with Alonzo for 6 more. Bryan found his high heels and was on the runway in great fabulous form.  Silver connected with Billy K for a TD. Top that with an XP2 to DMitch. The game was well balanced. With time running out, Silver was advancing the ball, and the clock won. One more play or one more minute and this might have been Silver’s game.
results_3_comment: Gold put it's undefeated season against a Milk Men squad returning captain Miles Simpson the field. White got off to a great 12-0 start buoyed by an INT by Greg Kenderdine and Paul G and Nolan TD's but the game was one-sided from there.  Kyle Butts led his squad on steady drives down the field and ran in a TD and threw another to Cameron. O.J. had his (3rd??!) INT of the season rushing making a great athletic play to turn the game around for the roDs.  In the 2nd half, Gold kept applying the pressure with 2 more Cameron TD's and another by Adam Strasberg.  John Clemons added an INT for good measure and the Gold team is 2 weeks away from the league's 2nd ever undefeated regular season!
results_4_comment: After a tough loss to Gold, White bounced back against the lesser metal, the Silver team.  Helping his own cause with an opening drive INT, Brandon Waggoner spread TD love to Rudy, Nolan and Stu to go up 20-0. But Silver wasn't to be stopped, scoring at the end of the half to DMitch. Mike Osorio added another 2 TD's in the second half, and Billy Kramer stretched the field but the defense couldn't get any stops and the hole was dug too big.  Newcomer Dan Van Roekel made the scoreboard for the first time with a headsy pick 6 to put away the game, and then scored an offensive TD for good measure.  Rudy added 2 INT's in the White victory.
results_5_comment: Teal QB Bryan S was riding a wave from San Diego Gaybowl and Hanging 10 on some lessons from Teal’s previous game in the day. Determined to prove his team relevant, he figured it out with a confident performance that, if nothing else, depended on his ability to dance down the field for enough yards to make to Devonta Freeman jealous. But he made good use of all the tools in the shed:  TD and XP to Ken G got things started. Gary R, reigniting his best Old School performance, put up another TD. QB Bryan swiveled his best hips for an XP. Also from the lost-n-found collection was Aaron Y who topped off the half with a confident catch for 6 more. Maroon struggled to find the D that could contain the Teal Zeal. Dancing out of the pocket all game, Bryan commanded respect. Larry W refused to take have a goose egg for the first half by putting up 6 for his team. But the lack of defensive might left them at a halftime deficit. True to form, Maroon QB Adam R came out in second half with a newfound focus. Maroon captain Justin P, challenged his team to put up the fight. Justin led by example with rushing and catches. While his Maroon’s D suffered with too much space in the middle, they exploited Teal at the same shortcoming. Open in the deep middle, QB Robbins found Larry W and supplemental star Dane S with a catch-n-dash to the end zone. A controversial pass interference call that wasn’t flagged might have meant another 2 points for the XP conversion attempt. Teal Bryan S proved that he can do more than dance on O and bars and speakers. He pulled down an INT and then scrambled for a TD. XP to Gary for a little more love. Using smarts and help from Captain Z, Bryan mastered the pitch-forward-pitch-back method of stacking up rushing yards. Another TD for him and another to Ken G. Teal came out ready to fight and came out solid winners. Maroon Will L? Come home. Your team needs you.
results_6_comment: Forest struck first in this game on a deep TD to Andy Larson (who also scored in the 2nd half).  Mike Hess added an INT before getting injured and the Humps went up two scores on a Tyler Fox run in. Will Jackson added another first half INT. Baby Blue bounced back, getting two TD's into Justin Mezetin's hands and Scott Graham added his own INT to keep the game close at 21-14.  Forest pulled away in the 2nd half spreading 3 more TD's to Garret B., James D., and Andy Larson.  While Josh Richards and Tyler Lacy (with 2) added TD's to the board for Baby Blue, they could not overcome 2 more INT's thrown by Scott Graham - to Rachel B and another to Will.  Forest marches one step closer to the #1 seed in the division.
results_7_comment: This love affair between Forest Hump’s Captain Chris C and QB Tyler has gotten Chase’s approval. “This truple works as long as you win and keep it on the field. You can “score” with Tyler, but that’s it. Only on the field.” And that romance continues with Forest Humps dominating this game over Navy. The first half seemed fairly balanced with Navy trailing only by a touchdown. TD by Navy newbie Christain S put them on the scoreboard. Forest’s first TD went to Will with the XP going to Garrett. Then another TD to—wait—Will again. Tyler put up the XP. Were they hustling Navy all along? Stick to the land and not the sea, and you’ll find a winning team—and a winning season so far—in Forest. The second half belonged to the Humpers as they evaded the waterlogged Navy. Is there a foursome at hand? Add Will to that truple and it’s a mixed medley. Will crushed with 2 TDs and an XP. Garrett, owning the center, had 2 more TDs and an XP. QB Tyler showed his chops on D with an INT and a TD. Is Navy still out at sea. QB Tony connected with Porter and an XP to Jon P. Too many holes to plug on that Navy ship and Forest found ‘em. Hump hump hump…Forest did a seek-n-destroy over Navy.
results_8_comment: Black has won their first game!  They didn't make this one look close going up 14-0 in the first half behind a Linda Pratt Pick-6 and offensive TD by Clevenger.  Kevin Moran added a 2nd half TD and Honeycuttt ran one in in to put the game away.  While Baxter and Cody Barry added 2nd half TD's for Orange, they couldn't overcome two more INT's in the second half to Captain / QB pair Honeycutt and Clev.  Baxter added an INT of his own in the 2nd half.
results_9_comment: On a day of really good games, this was no exception.  At the half, Navy was in the lead despite lots of dropped passes. QB Tony S, in vintage form, called the right plays but the players didn’t bring the hands. They brought the mimosas. Captain Porter salvaged his teammates’ drops by making some key catches. But W. Coachman made it right with a TD. And Tim A sang a lovely song with his XP. Graphite QB Mark H took the mic—and the ball—and rushed up and down the scales for his own TD. “I can name that tune and it’s called “Six Points.”” Stay Puff Dan S added to the chorus of TD’s for Graphite. Navy wasn’t deterred. They answered with a TD to Sam S and an XP to Will C. Staying focused on D, Navy pulled down an INT to maintain the halftime lead. Was that Tim A singing “I’ll Take You There?” The sing-off continued in the second half with both teams stretching their ranges. Graphite’s Mark H was a familiar tune. Scoring a TD. Barry chimed in on the tune with his on. An XP by Mark H was like a song on a repeat loop. We’ve heard that song before. Daniel H brought some harmony to this chorus with an INT. Morse added some vocals with an XP. Daniel H? Was that a TD for you? From the Navy team, TD’s went to Christian and W. Coachmen with a respectable rendition of “Ebony and Ivory”. QB Tony tickled the ivories for an XP. The tune—and the clock—ran out with them finishing in a minor key. Graphite takes this sing-along.
results_10_comment: Lime's losing streak continued to 6 straight games with a bitter defeat to the Purple Drank.  Matt Cline enjoyed his biggest offensive output of the season putting up 47 points across the day, helped by the 4 INT's his defense came up with over the course of the day.  Brad Allen had a first half INT and Lane Marshall had the lone 1st half TD for Lime.  For Purple - TD's and INT's rained like wildfire.  Jack Miles, Ryan Boyle and Patrick Menasco all scored in the first half while Jack grabbed 2 INT's as well.  In the second half?  Pretty much the same as the first.  QB's traded INT's to each other - Adam and Matt each catching one thrown by the other guy.  Jack Miles grabbed his 3rd INT on the day and a 2nd TD (HOW DID HE NOT WIN MVP?!).  Earl Armstrong scored 2 TD's in the 2nd half to seal the blowout.  Dameron and Long Diep scored for Lime, all the while asking, "MopTop won't you come play with us?!"
results_11_comment: Black wasn't done yet, going 2-0 on the day and putting target marks on a first round bye in the playoffs.  In a physical game, Black rode the momentum from their first game to gp 25-14 in the first half behind Honey's 2 TDs and Butters and Clev TDs.  The offensive outburst was buoyed by 2 INT's in the first half by Butters and Honey.... mmmmmmm English Muffins....  While Staci and Lacy (Aww isn't that cute) scored in the first half for Baby Blue, the game's offensive explosion slowed to a grinding halt in the 2nd half.  Scott Graham ran in a 2nd half TD to put the game within 3 points, but neither team was able to outwit their opponents defense going scoreless for the rest of the game. Black's season is redeemed and Baby Blue has some work to do going into the last two weeks.
results_12_comment: With high octane fuel in their engines, Red Rockets blasted off and didn’t look back in this take-it-to-the-stars win. Maroon just ran on an empty tank in this lopsided match. QB Sheerod found a star in the constellations with Jared L scoring two TD’s and 2 XPs. Howard and his QB Sheerod led their crew through orbit with dazzling displays from Alex P and Billy B. Catch a falling star in the way of INT’s and you’ve got Vikas, Sheerod, and Billy putting some love in their pockets. At the half, they were full throttle with 35 points on the board. Maroon was still at the pump filling up a leaky tank managing only 7 points. Straight off of an oil change and new spark plugs, Vikas managed two TD’s in the second half. Alex P added some anti-gravity work of his own and putting an XP on the map. For Maroon, Larry W was the lonely astronaut floating around on that field. TD for him. At the end of this space odyssey, it was Maroon sitting on the launching pad, “Houston, we have a problem.”
results_13_comment: In an attempt to cause referee Chris M. to turn to hard drugs and alcohol, Kelly Green and Brown engaged in a verbal and physical battle that rivaled nothing else we've seen this season.  Insults were issued, curse words flowed like whitewater, and Lord's names were taken in vain.  And Football happened too!  Kelly led 13-6 at the half behind TD's by Josh G. and Matt Nix.  Our very own Sam Smallwood added an INT.  Captain Kozak scored the game's first TD for Brown.  In the second half, Sam added a TD to go up 20-6, while Brown mounted a comeback.  A TD for newbie Evan Binder and one more by the Cap'n.  The two point conversion attempt failed, so the game went back into Kelly's hands and Marvin successfully led the team to drain the clock with creative play calling and athleticism for Kelly to get back to .500 on the season.

results_0_comment: Let the games begin with the new Supplemental Players. Dameron was there  suited up in Lime. But did both teams decide to sit out the first half? Having drinks with the refs? No stats for either team in the first half.  Come second half, this game took on a new face. Baxter put up 6 with Captain Sparrow following with an XP. Leading the spirit and points to the board for Lime, Dameron found 6 in the end zone.  Newbie Greg Kline helped his Orange team with a TD. QB Kyle found his own way to the end zone.  Mabray iced the cake when QB Kyle connected with him for 2 point conversion. Another 6. But Long D decided  that was enough. He pulled an INT down for the Lime team. QB Adam, looking for love in all the right places, gave 6 more reasons for Dameron to cheer. Orange wasn’t done. We’ve got a game going here. Orange QB Kyle was able to make his captain look good. Sparrow put up a TD. An even battle with Orange edging out the win.
results_1_comment: Kelly came in this game severely undermanned due to injury and work conflicts  and struggled against the undefeated Red Rockets.  Sheerod spread the ball around with TD's to Vikas, PJ and Jared Lucas - and Sheerod helped his own cause with a first possession INT as well as Matt Gander's INT.  Eduardo added a sack for the Rockets.  Nothing on the scoreboard for Kelly Green, who's sideline was supportive despite the 18-0 opening.  The second half was more even. Alex Payne added to the TD receivers, and PJ and Jared adderd two more.  Eduardo and Gander pulled in the sacks.  Josh Grossman had his first TD for Kelly, and Marvin, carrying the load for the depleted Kelly Team did cartwheels and pirouettes on his way into the end zone on a run.   The acrobatics were on display, but it was unfortunately in a lost effort.  Kelly falls to 2-2.
results_3_comment: Not much for letting people catch the ball, this defensive game only saw one INT all day (by Chris Hobbs), but the ball hit-the-ground aplenty.  Hotchkiss ran in a TD to start the scoring of for Power Blue, while Lipovsky and Overbeck put the Maroon Swear Words up 12-6 at the half.  An extremely well rested Lipovsky added a 2nd half TD to put Maroon clearly in control.  The Liberal Elite was not going to go down without a fight.  Tackney added a TD score and at 19-13 the game had a chance to be a dogfight.  But unfortunately, it seems as though the Liberal Elite had taken too much for granted, not letting no-show Sean Holihan know about their deep brewing scandal.  Maroon's familiar progressivism won out as the fans on the sideline shook their head and wished they had never fallen in love so much with the Elite in the first place.
results_4_comment: What started off as a football game ended up in a rigorous debate between two candidates running for new DCGFFL board position, Director of Complaints.  Representing Liberal Alabama, Honeycutt donned black and squared off against the staunch conservative from North Dakota, Matt Pearce.  The friction on the stage was palpable.  Pearce's border control policy was on display as he ran in the game's first TD and fired another to Border-Patroller Walter to go up 14-0.  But Honeycutt would not let Pearce get away with keeping all the illegals out.  Clevenger answered with his own TD and there was life for the Blacklisted.  Stern endorsed the Bison by adding a TD of his own and Honeycutt stammered when asked about his Planned Parenthood Policy.  Down 24-8, Pearce stumbled, sacked by Thomas Leonard.  Trying to gain favor of the refs, he pointed to the Black Captain.  "You can't let her win.  Look at that face!" he screamed.  Clevenger calmly answered "I think women all over Carter Barron heard what Pearce said."  INT for Clev.  Unfortunately, he wasn't able to deliver a final punchline and the half ended.  The second half of the debate was very one-sided as Pink was able to uncover some secret e-mails sent by Honeycutt from his personal e-mail server.  "Dear Justie-poo.  You're the bestest and I love you.  Let's buy a house and never play this mean sport again and live happily ever after."  Pick 6 by Capolla.  Walter and Capolla each added another TD as Honeycutt floundered on stage.  Honey represented Bama strong and punched in two more TD's.  Fellow short-blonde competitor was not going to let a comeback bid happen though.  Crazy Uncle Ryan Stitt delivered the final game sealing interception and the Pink team runs away with the nomination.
results_5_comment: Oldest League MVP ever?  Brian Donohoe is making his case by scoring 2 TD's in the first half against a winless Black Squad.  The addiition of Butters didn't allow the team to win its first game, nor did his INT and TD in the first half.   Honey threw two of his own, both to Gerard.  Leaf was up 13-6 at the half and poured it on in the second.   Steve '2 yards at a time' Gong added another TD and Derrick had 2 sacks with an INT.  P-Paw keeps racking up the stats.  Another TD For him.  Gerard told us all that he throws a lot of interceptions, but at least he is fun.  Where is the other half of the deal?  Black can't get healthy soon enough, Honey ran in a TD and Anthony and Tom assisted with sacks, but the losses are starting to pile up.
results_6_comment: Baby Blue changed their diapers and advanced to training wheels in this solid victory over Navy. Neither team could quite wake up from nap time as everything seemed to happen in the second half.  Like Bert and Ernie, Baby Blue Q Scott and Captain Jerrell said,”Who needs 7 players, we can run the entire O by ourselves.”  Counting TD’s in Count Dracula style Jerrell 1,2,3,4 TD’s in the first half alone and 1,2 XPs. “Wanna buy a vowel to go with those numbers?” Scott added his own 1-2-3-4-5-6 to his counting skills with his own TD. Peter  P and Scott sang  “Two of these things are not like the others” as they each pulled down INT’s. Navy was as happy as the Grouch when they couldn’t keep pace. TD’s to Sam S and XP to Will C gave them a treat from the Cookie Monster. But no milk to wash down this defeat. Captain Porter politely yanked a sack and sang “Come and Play. Everything’s A-OK.”
results_7_comment: Fecal Mattered (or was it extra points?) in this close game where Gold erased an early 12-6 deficit to come back and win by 2 points.  The roDs started off strong with an INT on the first drive by Kyle Butts, helping his own cause. He drove down and pumped a TD pass to Cameron Burrell.  Fueled by another stalled drive by Brown, Gold looked fully in control of the game until captain Joe chest-bumped a would-be TD pass into opponent Mike D'Ignazio's hands.  The tables seemed to turn.  Andy Pratt and his army of Oompa Loompas marched down the field and he ran in a TD.  Brown followed up with a stellar defensive stop of their own behind sacks by Newbie Evan Binder and consistent threat Mecha.  Andy fired his first TD pass of the day to Austin Plier and Brown looked in control with a 12-6 halftime lead.  But the roDs erected a comeback.  Kyle Butts, jealous of the steam behind Andy's booty, ran in for his own TD and then an XP try.  The roDs got familiar with their own sack plan and unleashed Adam Strasberg and Matt Barnes on the Prattster to come up with a couple stops of their own.   The Browns got the ball back and a TD by Adrian Morales put them up 5 points, but the Browns couldn't convert.  Gold drove back and drained the clock doing it, culminating in a game winning TD to Cameron as the team remained undefeated.
results_8_comment: Determined to come out for its first win, Urine Trouble showed up in big numbers for the first time this season having suffered injuries and absences. They added supplemental Jack B to their armory. Maroon had a fire-up squad and determined leadership in Captain Justin and QB Adam R. Power Yellow QB Jim C kickstarted his new supplemental player with a TD. And newbie Kieran put up the XP. But Maroon shrugged. Piling up points in the first half to his capable squad, QB Adam, spewed balls to Will L, Larry W, and Justin P twice.  XP’s to Justin P, Sean B, and QB Adam danced in for two of his own. Matt P piled on more sacks to his collection of stats. How does she do it? Eager to relieve themselves QB Jim shook it off and found TD’s in Enrique and Jacob W. Banged up Kieran delivered another XP. Feeling some momentum building, Power Yellow went into overtime outperformed by 14 points but fired up about their game. In the second half, Urine Trouble decided to get serious. QB Jim found his groove and delivered TD’s to Marlon and Chris R playing on a banged up foot. Captain JJ delivered an XP. Chris R maintained his reputation as sly and reliable with his weekly INT. Kieran put up yet another TD. And new Jack wrapped up the strong second half with 6 more.  This game headed to OT. Tempers high and efforts strong, both teams fought with loaded guns. Each team scored on its drive from the 20. Maroon  took advantage of a penalty and scored from the 2 ½ on the XP attempt. The marathon game went to Maroon by 2 in double overtime.
results_9_comment: The battle of the Precious Metals meant Silver polishing up its team and coming out against the shiny  Gold.  Old, but not tarnished, Steve A put up the first TD for Silver followed by XP to Michelle. Showing bling in his skills, John C snagged an INT and added more to his war chest of stats. Cam had his own shining moments with two back to back TD’s for Gold. Back in the Silver Dept, Captain Donald weighed Gold. Cam and Kyle and John each took six to Ft. Knox. Cam, Kip, and Kyle put XP’s around their necks. Levert  J added currency to the piggy bank with a TD.  Ounce for ounce, it was respectable of silver, but gold came out with all the booty.
results_11_comment: This battle of two top-ranked teams was one of the biggest games of the weekend.  Determined to continue their winning streaks, both teams lit up the first half with a back-n-forth rally with Graphite eeking out a 1 point advantage of 14-13. For Graphite, I’m-too-pretty-just-admire-me Rob C got things started for QB Hofberg with a TD. Captain Chris M put up the XP. But out of the Forest, Tyler F connected with speedie AJ who dashed through the trees and into the end zone. 6 points.  Forest rusher James D pull down a sack on QB Mark. Unphased,QB Mark  gave his captain something to yell about—other than the refs—when he put six points on the board. Barry M increased the love with an XP. “Dude, this mountain climb isn’t over. It takes a lot to get on the top of me,” from QB Tyler. He did the hokie-pokie in for 6, turned it all around and went back in for XP.  Move over  Chris M, teammate Dan S wants some of the love. TD for him. QB Mark added to the heap with six more. Will J helped the Forest fire with his TD and Garrett fueled the flame with his XP. Forest fire contained by Graphite: 26-20. But there’s something smoldering under there.
results_12_comment: Both teams stumbled into each of their double headers building on momentum from the first game but also showing the effects of fatigue. Benefitting from the sneaky efforts of small people, Austin and Mike D dashed around the field like Lilliputians running between legs and under furniture. Both put TD’s on the board for Brown. The paramedics were waiting on the sideline with stretcher for Captain K.  False alarm as  he managed to get an XP without tearing his labia. For Urinators, QB Jim dashed in for a TD and Marlon—actually catching a ball—put up six more. “Was I suppose to hold onto that? Or drop it?”  Beserker Sean G came to the game bringing lots of love and encouragement for both teams. “I love you. And I love you. Let’s have lunch. After I break your @#%! neck.” Called out by refs for excessive love, he became enraged as his unrequited romantic advances went unanswered. “I’ll make you love me mutherf###er.”  In the second half, Brown Q  delivered his own love by using pitch plays and making use of various players to take the lead. Ready for some group love, Andy P blew kisses all over the field. Yellow Q Jim C shared some love to opposing Captain by throwing an INT directly to him. “Here Sweetheart…this is for you, my love.”  Captain K returned the love by sacking Yellow Q.  Power Yellow found some love in Jack B. But the lovefest was over. Tempers flew, refs shouted, hearts were broken and class rings were given back. “Sorry I don’t love you anymore.” This romance is over with Brown winning the love affair: 27-18.
results_13_comment: Taken out drinking the night before, extremely straight QB Bryan Sanders thought he would puke in the opening huddle.  He ended up having his best performance as QB to date.  Evading sacks and buying time in the pocket, he spread TD's amongst Z, Ken Green, Gary Reboca and Alonzo in the first half.  Steady pressure and tempers aflare by Teal rattled the Milk Men who lost their first game of the season despite TD's by Nolan, Rudy and Gabe.  Despite an INT by Gabe in the 2nd half, the Milk Men couldn't deliver the goods.  Brett Chambers and Alonzo added 2nd half TD"s and what was supposed to be a close game for standings positioning ended up being a blowout.
