results_0_comment: In a battle between our beloved power ranking pundits, Captains Patrick Kozak and Donald Mitchell laced it up for our inaugural Friday Night Lights game at King Greenleaf Fields.  Interestingly enough, the two of them just shouted Power Rankings lines at each other the entire game.  "You can't stop Michelle T. you can only hope to contain her!" as she marched into the end zone for the game's opening TD.  "Who needs Billy Kramer?" was screamed out as Osorio and Dmitch put up 2 more TD's to go up 18-6.  But Brown stormed back led by their staunch defense.  Kozak earned 2 sacks and Sam Hewitt earned another to shut our Silver in the 2nd half.  Meanwhile, Andy Pratt got into a rhythm and spread 4 TD's to Diggy, Austin, Mecha, Newbie Kyle V. and ran one in himself.   "How does team twink keep scoring on the pitch play?" Dmitch asked.  Drewtiful earned MVP for Silver for a 2nd half INT that should have sealed the game, and also not beating anyone up.
results_1_comment: In the DCGFFL’s  inaugural game under the lights at King Greenleaf Recreation Center, it was only fitting Chris C.’s Forest Humps were triumphant over Clay A’s Purple Drank. Quarterback Tyler F. and Matt C. traded touchdowns in the first half: respectively to Garret B. and Mike H.; Jack M. and Andrew C. In the second, Forest ran away with three unanswered touchdowns including the game’s final to Will J.
results_2_comment: Liberal  Elite’s (Power Blue) captain, Sean H said “Let’s act like that game didn’t happen. I mean, can we all just be gay and drink and love one another and work towards liberal causes?” Perhaps captain. But finish this game first. Scoreboard didn’t reflect the challenges that went into this game.  For Power Blue, Dennis M managed to pull down an INT in his solid all-around game. QB Hotch connected with a few liberal-leaning passes but otherwise felt the strains of a tough rush. Kelly’s Captain did his best to referee the game AND play at the same time.  Well done Captain. Kelly managed to control the first half but fell below its anticipated domination. But slow and steady wins the race was the mantra with some help from Power Blue QB. Two INTs were found by Marvelous Marvin and another by Sam S. Power Blue had enough D to prevent a complete blow-out. By end of half, Kelly had only one TD to Peter S and XP to Sam. Sacks by Sequoia and Ryan S. proved they had the control of this game.  Kelly Captain came down with his own TD and left the game victorious and injured.
results_3_comment: Teal Captain Mike Z is coaching up his team in typical fashion. “Gurl, you’ll get use to that drag outfit in no time. You need more sass in your passing game and more dazzle on the runway.” “You’ll learn to looovvee that wig and heels.” “Does this dress make me look fat? ‘’from QB Bryan S. “I think I play better in this teal number? Is it my color?” In first half she proved that drag queens can play football. She connected with Alonzo Maybelina for 6 and Smiffy for an XP. Then in his best heels, QB Bryanna dash in for 6 more and an XP for flair. Double snapping over her head with “How was that bitches?” Red Rockets seemed unfazed. They blasted off with J. Lucas in the first half putting two TD’s and an INT in her purse. Red QB Iman Sheerod sashayed down the field in her usual swagger. He delivered more love to Vikas for an XP and PJ followed with six more pennies in his clutch. Second half went full throttle as the Red Rockets took control. Billy B found two TDs. PJ added some XP love and a little rouge for color. The scores kept going. Teal answered with Teriyaki fashion. Two TD’s for her. “That’s a drag queen!” “Did my wig intimidate you?” Loudest drag queen in history, Ken G put up more fabulousness with his XP and QB Bryanna werked it for 6 more. But not enough to outperform the Red Rockets. Project Runway to continue.
results_4_comment: Baby Blue Me’s Peter P. and the Bottomless’ Mimosa’s Baxter O. starred in Sunday’s showdown, trading touchdowns all morning. Peter’s three first half scores and two extra point conversions keyed the team’s 20-7 halftime lead. Neither Baxter’s two in the second, nor his quarterback Kyle M’s late interception, were enough to undo blues’ first half work.
results_5_comment: Whu whu WHUUUTT? Black Teamer Linda P snags an INT from Graphite QB Mark H? Move over Andy P. Otherwise this was a mismatched game of strengths. The David and Goliath tale was over at that.  Graphite stomped around and wrote this story. QB Mark H spread the ball with ease—and style points—to Barry M and nearly anyone on Graphite wanting to catch a ball. Barry for 6 followed by XP to Rob C. Hofberg in true biblical proportion scored his own 6 and snagged an INT and then ate some matzo ball soup. XP to Sam B. After a halftime of loxs and bagels and gefilte fish and drinking Manischevitz, the Jewish led invasion kept up the unholy march. Second half, frogs and locust besieged Black as  Hofberg led his team to the Promise Land and end zone. TDs to Rob C and Dan S. Rob C added value with XP and INT. Honberg with another XP. Sacks by Barry M, Andrew E, and Sam B ensured that Graphite beat the bejesus out Black. “Who’s that funny man dressed in white causing all this traffic? Pope? Is that his name?” from Mark H. “Say, who’s the skinny guy on the cross?”
results_6_comment: After a grueling early win over the Liberal Elties, Peanut Butter Kelly Time gimped through the second half of their double header with Teal-or Swift. Behind fresh-armed quarterback Brian S, Teal-or scored three first half touchdowns to Brett C. and Kevin S: Captain Chris C’s hobbled squad was held scoreless. Kelly’s Sam S. notched the team’s lone touchdown. Sacks by quarterback Marvin W. and Aras T. weren’t enough to stop Brian from adding second half scores on the ground and through the air to Brett.
results_7_comment: The Red Rockets fired on all cylinders against Power Blue Sunday. Sherrod W’s tactful attack led to two touchdowns on the ground and to Alex P. and Patrick T through the air. Two costly red zone interceptions thrown by Brian H. to Jared L. stalled Power Blue comeback drives in the first and second halves. Captain Sean H. and Matt M. notched the Liberal Elite’s only two scores.
results_8_comment: The Slips arrived with all their usual pride and arrogance and wearing a pretty shade of pink. “Of course we’ll win.” from Pink QB Matt P. “How do I look in this shade of pink?” And to start that victory march, Matt P threw an interception by way of a tipped pass. Pink came out shy on players but not on might. Ryan S yanked a solid sack for Pink. “I love pink. It’s my favorite verb. Yea me. Did you see that?  I got a sack.” Ummhmm. We got it. Matt P redeemed his INT with his own scramble for 6. But Lime wasn’t taking the Pink Slip. Two TD’s in the first half. One to MopTop and the other to Brad A. Is this an upset? Pink responded to newbie Max R with a TD and XP2.  The Power of the Pink proved too much for Lime in the second half. With adjustments to D, Pink went for a don’t-look-back gusto. Captain Sean S added two INT’s to his stats (as he humbly reminded us.) Max R plucked another INT from the less-than-glowing Lime team and then refused to stop. TD and XP2. Michael G brought muffins and 6 points to the Pink team and Matt S. piled on. That QB Matt sure looks Pretty In Pink. A solid win for Pink 40-12.
results_9_comment: Maroon moved past the Golden RoD’s all-glow, no-show defense in the first half. Quarterback Adam R. drove by Captain Joe H’s defense for two early scores. Jason W.’s 2 interception returns amounted to a 19-0 halftime lead. The resilient rods, however, polished themselves off and shone bright in the second half. Twenty unanswered points on three consecutive drives from Kyle Butts, Adam S., and Cameron., including a crucial go-ahead extra point, erased the halftime deficit. Persistent pressure from rookie O. J. held Maroon scoreless and a late-game interception by Kyle Butts. sealed Gold’s comeback
results_10_comment: Missing their new stud, Wil, Navy struggled early and often and Gerard had his best game as a QB (maybe?  No INT's!?) to earn a blowout victory for Leaf.  Tony spread 4 INT's to Gerard, Clay, Brian D and Trevor in the opposing QB effort.  Newbie Christian Smith scored Navy's opening TD and earned a sack to win his first MVP of his career.  On the opposite end, Brian Donohoe ran a clinic and had 2 TD's in the first half en route to his first MVP this season. Also scoring for Leaf were Gong, P-Paw and BB.
results_11_comment: In an even more depleted lineup following the win over Lime, Pink fought hard in this back and forth battle.  Orange led most of the way, up 22-14 at half until Pink had scored on their first drive and had a defensive stop on the first Orange possession of the second half.  Max Rothschild could not be stopped scoring 3 deep plays on the day.  The game came down to the last two minutes with Orange leading a methodical drive down the field doing everything right, getting out of bounds on short plays and key first downs on 3rd and 4th down.  With a minute remaining Orange had made their way to the redzone with two time outs remaining and Pink on their heels with only 7 defenders able to play.  With Orange able to run over ten plays from the redzone, Pink made a gritty stand preventing Orange from scoring through the remaining time and 3 plays at the end of the game by putting a ton of pressure on McKinney and solid coverage behind them.
results_12_comment: It was a battle of the bodily fluids - Milk and Urine and despite a lot of blood and tears, neither team seemed passionate about the game's outcome. White took down an undermanned Urinal team and broke the seal in the last two minutes to make it appear less competitive than the game really was.  The first half ended 6-0 White with a breast-fed TD to Nolan.  Each team had the ball twice and a lot of clock was drained but both team's encountered shy bladders.  Gabe A. and Kieran each came down with INT's.  Brandon ran in a TD in the first possession of the 2nd half to go up 2 scores but the Urinals flushed back with TD's to Marlon and Kieran to make it 14-12 (Extra points matter).  The Milk Men filled up with another TD to Nolan but they couldn't make it a 2 possession game.  With two minutes left, Yellow sputtered out in their comeback bid and the Milk Men responded with a TD to Miles and a game-finishing pick 6 by Nolan.

results_0_comment: Titan-sized teams led by Marc Hofberg and Gerard Burley clashed in their season openers. Both sides’ defenses were stalwart strong: Hofberg was sacked by Leaf’s Matt Hunter and Burley and pressured into an Brian Donohoe interception; Graphite’s Rob Casey returned an interception for a touchdown. In the second half, Graphite stood taller on Andrew Esquer’s relentless rush, Hofberg’s touchdown scramble, and Barry Mauck’s scoring catch. Brandon Benjamin found the endzone twice for Leaf.
results_1_comment: Bottomless Mimosas (Orange), still drinking bottomless mimosas, and still pondering their bottom status. The mimosas served them well in the first half as they contr olled this game. JP wasted no time reminding everyone that he’s a strong rusher. He sacked the scrappy Forest QB Tyler F.  Quick and sly as a fox, Tyler couldn’t escape the JP. Another mimosa for you. “No ma’am you drunks” as Captain Cormier answered with an INT.  But it didn’t slow down the drunken progress of the Bottomless. From newbie Greg C., “What’s with all this talk of bottoms and bottomless mimosas? I’m straight.” Immune to the effects of chronic gay drinking, newbie, and presumed straight,”  he proved he’s all about the game bringing down a TD and an XP in first half. “I don’t want your girly drink. Get me a pretty pink cosmo.” QB Kyle M. ( or is it Pendersumpin?) managed to add 6 more to the pile. TD for him. “I love this game. What are we playing?” from Mike H. on Forest Hump. “This game looks familiar. Is it like checkers?” He managed a TD in the first half and again in the second. Will J. threw in some love with an XP is the first half for The Humps. But the continued drinking brought down the Orange team in the end. While Captain Sparrow was at Carter Barron field playing in a tournament of Panties Exchange (or tennis?), his team lost their momentum. The Humpers mounted a fight. Coming back in second half, fully lubed and wearing no protection, they outperformed Orange. Points on the scoreboard by James D, Tyler L. and Mike H. “Yahtzee. And now I crown my checker and call your Boardwalk.” Newbie AJ? “He’s a baller and we want to see his balls” from Forest Team. Orange’s Jake C. and Greg C managed to show respect in the second half but it wasn’t enough. Victory for Forest Hump. Sparrow, get your birdass off the court and in the right game. Orange MVP: Jake C. Forest MVP: Mike H.
results_2_comment: With backup QB and captain Jason Clevenger starting the game for #Blacklisted, the Black Offense got off to a quick start with a TD to Bill Klitz to tie the game early 6-6.  Injuries to Nikki Kasparek and Bill Klitz took the wind out of their sails quickly (Get better soon!) and allowed Glow Your Roll to ride MopTop strong, who had 2 more TD’s for the fluorescent team.  Kevin Moran and Jim R. both scored in the second half for Black, but it was too little too late as Adam Martin had given Lime a comfortable lead by then.  Long, MopTop and Mystery Teammate (write legibly refs!) picked off Clev for 3 total interceptions and Clev added his own late in the game, but it was not enough as Black suffered a devastating start to their season.
results_3_comment: In the most competitive game of the day, Red prevailed in overtime with a 1-point conversion catch by captain, Howard Yuan.  You would have thought with all the bodies flying all over the field, each team was using Rockets or Bullets respectively to gain an advantage over their opponent.  Silver compiled 6 sacks on Sheerod and Co., 4 by Marcus Kendrick and 2 by Mike Osorio.  Levert racked up more stats in one game than all of last season with 3 TD’s and an INT for the Bullets (who may change their name to the Wizards halfway thru the season).  Sheerod spread out 5 TD’s to Jared Lucas, Howard, newcomer Billy Buntin and 2 to PJ Tangney for the Rockets.  Sparring and spitting, Alex Payne and Drew Halunen maimed everyone on the field en route to 2 INT’s and a TD respectively.
results_4_comment: To Bleach or not to Bleach?  That was the question.  The White Team spent the first half milking rookie QB, Andy Pratt with 2 INT’s from Rudy Legg Benividas.  Brandon Waggoner capitalized with 2 TD throws to Nolan and another to Rudy to go up 19-0, despite Mecha Santos’ consistent pressure, including a sack.  Refusing to be a starfish in the second half, the Brown offense started to get in a rhythm and move the ball more consistently, but their defense allowed The Milk Men to keep on churning with TD’s by Greg K. and John Santanella.  Finally, at the end of the game, the TouchBrowns lived up to their namesake with a blazing quick TD run by Austin Plier and circus catch conversion by captain, Patrick Kozak to avoid being milked dry for the day.
results_5_comment: The Baby Battles Begin. Freshly changed diapers, these two teams woke from a night on the nipple and went to play patty-cake patty-cake. But the dominant team came out in the Color Pink. Defying the girl color, Pink was in control. Baby Huey QB Matt P. made Playdoh of his opponents. Using Max R, Matt P, and Sam C for TD’s in the first half, Pink didn’t need a fresh bottle or bath. But Baby Blue was wishing for a new play date. Baby Blue QB Scott G. found his new feet (and arm) to reach Staci P. right out of her Pack-n-Play. TD for her. Ricardo said, “I want that toy” and yanked off Pink QB flag. Sack. But it wasn’t enough. Pink, with pretty bows in their hair, dominated the playground. Walt S had two XP and Joe C said, “I made stinky but I also got an XP and and and and INT. Are you proud of me mommy?” Pink Team leader Sean S said, “There’s no nap time or treats till we win. Do well for Daddy. Call me Daddy.” He led the way with his own TD. Along with Michael G and Joe C. Walt and Sam C. both managed to yank away the toys with INT’s of their own.” Baby Blue couldn’t muster their First Steps in the second half. Captain Jerrell “ I want my mommy and teddy bear. This hurts worse than a spankin’. Can I have my binky now?” Everyone go to your corner.
results_6_comment: With only 8 players to field for their opening game, Sean Bartel put his undefeated quarterback streak on the line against the Peanut Butter Kelly Times.  Riding a first half TD to Matt Pesesky, and an INT by Larry Womack, Maroon Bitch Get Out Da Way kept things a respectable 14-6 at the half.  Kelly was buoyed by TD’s to Sam Smallwood and captain Chris Chernicki.  Kelly came out strong in the second half with a run in by QB Marvin Washington and INT’s by Peter Sima and newcomer Scott Williams to win the game over a depleted Maroon squad
results_7_comment: After edging out Orange by a leaf in Game 1 of their doubleheader, Forest quickly branched above and beyond Lime in Game 2. Four interceptions and six touchdowns spread across Tyler Fox, Mike Hess, Will Jackson, AJ Anderson, and Garrett Barincoat amounted in a 33-0 halftime score. Lime’s three second-half touchdowns -- an interception returned by Brendan McFarland, a run by Adam Martin, and a catch by Nick Christiansen -- weren’t enough to uproot Forest’s strong start.
results_8_comment: The Urine seemed ready to flow as this game started to go in this battle this penis-centric swordfight. Bill C. danced his way to a TD. Golden RoDs was having none of it. They needed no Viagra to improve their performance. The RoDs, fully throbbing with power, answered with a bigger stick.  The RoDs came thrusting back. QB Kyle, ready to top any battle, made good use of Cameron B. for a TD followed by an XP to the Famous Strasberg. Newbie O.J. came out to fight. Fast on the rush, he shoved into the Power Yellow offensive line with Fire-in-the-Hole determination netting a sack and non-stop aggressive sexual assault. He outwitted Urine Trouble QB with a quick reaction for an INT on a pitch play. Power Yellow’s K. Gostin wasn’t to be extinguished by the stiff threat. Newbie battled over and over, play after play, and fought for the ball to the ground in another play. Then, INT by Power Yellow newbie Sam S.  “You can’t ignore me.” And then grinned. Power Yellow QB said “I can’t hold this any longer “ and threw several more INTs over the course of the game. RoD’s straight boy, returning from a season off, wasn’t to be ignored. Kyle M. racked up 2 TD’s. With four injured players on the sideline for Power Yellow, they were limp. Jacob W. pulled it out when he scored for Power Yellow. But Gold penetrated every hole in the Power Yellow plan. Smart Gold QB Kyle B. used John C., Cameron, Kyle M. by spraying the ball in every direction. XP by DJ made was more proof that Gold is in this to dominate. (Thanks Gold Captain Joe for the input.)
results_9_comment: Straight off the manicure, this was a nail-biter. Both teams in this colorfield fought for the crown in this game. Captain Porter with veteran QB Tony set up the first half with a confident performance. Tony didn’t waste time using both Wills (there are two Will C.’s) in the domination of the first half. Will C (both of ‘em) were put to good use. Two TD’s for Will C. Tony managed to swagger in for 6 of his own. XP (2 point conversion) to Sam. Will snagged an INT. Was Purple just hustling them all along? Newbie QB Matt C. said, “You gays are pretty but I’m prettier.” He made his own magic by putting Earl to use. Two TD’s in the first half for him. XP to Ryan B. But this game isn’t over. “I think I’m in love” said QB Tony as he saw the love he was getting from both those Wills. Is this a threesome? Purple Captain wasn’t folding. “That Navy is going to sink in my drink” from Purple Drank QB. TD’s to Andrew C. and Cody G. XP2 to Jack M with all hair and beauty in place. “I love being fabulous and humble.”
results_10_comment: Dueling Br(y/i)ans -- Sanders and Hotchkiss -- were effective in their season debuts, marching their offenses downfield and tossing just one interception each. But the rookie Sanders excelled in the red zone, running for a score, tossing two to Alonzo Mable, and connecting deep with Brett Chambers. Matt Murtaugh’s late-game interception lead to the Elite's lone touchdown by Jasmyne Johnson.

results_0_comment: Gold continued their magical touch without QB Sheerod. Black has a shaky record but is picked for a lot of upsets in the playoff bracket!
results_1_comment: Lime's stingy defense held Black to just 6 points. But these are two teams that can go either way next week!
results_2_comment: Skyblue held in but ultimately fell to the mighty gold team. Sky might finally have a full roster for the playoffs and it's a 9 seed to be afraid of!
results_3_comment: Another heart breaker for Maroon who has had a less than successful season... but I see a disney movie in the making as they tear through the playoffs desipte the odds!
results_4_comment: A tight game featuring two solid teams who can both make some noise in the first week of may!
results_5_comment: Another nail-biter here as BO takes some positive momentum into the playoffs while Purple looks to right the ship after a few losses!
results_6_comment: Navy is getting hot, and just in time! Greg K has this team preped and ready for the playoffs. Vegas had a tough time making up for the loss of QB Scott G. Jamar W did his best Colin Kapernick impression and Chirs M looked like Ben Rothlesberger taking snaps for Vegas.
results_7_comment: Two offensive juggernauts went down to the last play with Power Blue finishing on top. Both of these teams have championship potential but also have some head-scratching losses on the resume. This is will be a playoff rematch to keep an eye on sunday!
results_8_comment: This OT thriller featured a whole lot of scoring as Nikki K and her Thots prevailed over the LOD. Lets see what noise these teams can make this weekend!
results_9_comment: Many believe that this game was a preview of the championships... Matt P ran over the toes of Camo to a W and a 1 seed in the playoffs. Reigning Defensive MVP Mark H failed to intercept anything on D (for once) and that proved to be the difference.
results_10_comment: BO took full advantage of Vegas' woe's and turnt it up!  Jim C looked like he was in his 20's again, so watch out!
results_11_comment: Despite losing a tough OT match, Veteran Adam S amp'ed his team back up to defeat a tough Slate team. Patrick K is in unfamiliar territory having to play in the morning matchups of the playoffs!
results_12_comment: A close game in the first half turned into a blowout when the Ty-Ty connection struck again for Fuchsia. Tyler L is looking mighty impessive as Fuchisa is on a roll!
results_13_comment: In an offensive battle, it was newcomer Ausin P aka the Flash who came up with a late game pick to force OT and then made the game winning PAT to win one of the most intense Double OT games ever at Carter Barron.

results_0_mvp: Josh E. (Sky Blue), Mike H. (Power Blue)
results_0_comment: It was morphin time for the Green Rangers as they continued their run in front of a huge FNL crowd. The Power Rangers relied on a consistent offensive attack with Bill C, Sean H, Ryan S and Peter P all lighting up the scoreboard. Slate put up plenty of offense too but it was mostly in the 2nd half and was ultimately too little too slate.
results_1_comment: Down 7 at the half and 16 in the second half (35-19), one team looked to the sky for some intervention and they found it, as the Sky Sexuals stormed back to win 37-35 over the #2 ranked Power Blue squad.  Captain Kyle B. had 3 TDs, Gerard B. added 2, including the go-ahead score with 3 seconds left, and Josh E. had one of his own.  Larry W. and Capt. Jerrell P. each had 2tds in the loss, while Bornmann had 1.  This marks 8 straight FNL losses for you-know-who!
results_2_comment: This Friday Night Lights game came down to the end, with Navy notching another victory 21-18 to pull even on the season at 4-4.  Down by 9 late in the second half, Burnt Orange player Sam S. made a ridiculous over-the-shoulder grab to get his squad to within 3 points.  But, the Navy crew was able to run the clock out with smart clock management for the big V.  Burton and QB Jim C. had BO’s other scores.  Meanwhile, Mike C. (x2) and Levert had Navy’s TDs with QB Tyler running in the game-deciding 2 point conversion.
results_3_comment: Maroon QB Charlie L: “You don’t bring me flowers.” Maroon Captain Adam: “You don’t sing me love songs. Or bring me TD’s. Our bromance is over.” This FNL games turned into a solid match with Maroon being led by its Captain turned QB. It was their closest match all season with Adam R showing competency and smarts while advancing the ball down the field with short attack and crossing routes.  Where was the Purple defense?  The points on the board at the end of the half didn’t reflect the strong playing from Maroon. Adam R looked comfortable zinging the ball at Mike D and Andy A. Purple answered with Craig N snagging two INT’s in the first half. “You da fool to throw in my neighborhood.”  Quick costume change from D to O, Craig put on his QB outfit—and some dazzle-- as he ran in for a TD and connected with Howard Y for another.  Maroon didn’t give up. Maroon turned on the lights in the second half.  Adam met success with Andy A and Will C as they cashed in for two TD’s. Purple D held strong. Determined to break their losing streak, the Plum Dumpsters tightend up and held Maroon to the last two plays on the 8 yard line. Clay A proved he’s a reliable teammate on both sides of the ball. Great effort all around.
results_4_comment: An unlikely turn of events when Randy’s ballet class was adjourned for Gold Team when Sheerod pirouetted out of control and fell off pointe and broke his leg last weekend.  Fuschia took control of this dance and changed the ending of the performance.  Straight teammates were thrown off when the choreography was changed. “Why must the gays be the only ones doing ballet?” from Gold stand-in QB Bryan. “What about me?” from other straight John C. “Watch me…5,6,7,8…jete, jete, pas de bouree, pas de chat.”  In the first of this performance, Gold seemed like they were outdancing Fuschia as Big Will and John C did a pas de deux with the QB and boureed to the end zone. TDs for both.  But after intermission, Fuschia did an allegro while Gold was doing an adagio. The tempo changed as QB Tyler found his own dance partners in Tyler F, Trey P, Chris C and Will. They took control of this show and danced all around Gold Team’s Dying Swan. The standing ovation went to Fuschia for pulling off a remarkable feat. (See Randy S for all ballet translations and references.)
results_5_comment: In a game that showed what Royal can do when they are all there, Royal notched their 6th win to set up a battle Royale for the 1 seed next week with Camo.  And although Derrick J. did not show up in the score sheet, he definitely set the tone for the Royal defense, driving QB George G. nuts all day with his hard rushes.  Miles S. had 4 TDs on the day while Captain Moptop added Royal’s other 2 TDs.  Simeon had Power Yellow’s sole TD in the loss, 42-6.
results_6_comment: The scoreboard just doesn’t always show the whole picture.  In an ongoing  tough season Teal showed up for a strong game against one of the league’s most solid teams, Camo Grey. Though not many stats to show for itself, Teal was polishing its game. Dameron led the effort and said “No ma’am” to Camo Grey QB when he pulled down an INT. First half, belonged to Camo Grey as Mark H and Matt M twerked up and down the field scattering TD’s and passes.  At the half, Camo was in full control at 20-0. Teal wasn’t to be put down. Captain Jayme F and QB Peter D turned up the effort. Tim S and Jared chalked up TDs with XP by Dameron and TJ mustered up some hope when he pulled down an INT.  Camo stayed cool and in control. QB Mark connected with Andrew for A TD. Cole W continued his quest for more more more stats; INT and strong playing all around.
results_7_comment: In a match of two teams with strange team names, Neon Kingon's held-on in this marathon and won. Apparently everyone was still hung over from Saturday because most of the action came in the second half. Cody on Red and Rob on Lime took home team MVP honors, something that they are both getting used to. The real question is where will these two teams land in the playoff picture? Week 8 is going to be so exciting!!!
results_8_comment: EXTRA POINTS MATTER! Scott G is too much of a veteran to only convert one PAT, QB rookie John B on the other hand converted on two of three attempts and it proved to be the difference in the 1 point victory over power house Vegas gold. Perhaps Vegas' cards are showing and there is a formula to beating this stacked team? One more week to tune it up before the playoffs! If you're queasy, do yourself a favor and don't look at Kevin K's instagram photo of his broken finger, get well soon, but we all know you have 9 other good fingers to point at people while screaming on the field!
results_9_comment: Power Yellow had their four game win streak ended by Royal, but picked themselves right back up with a win over Silver (who had just defeated heavyweight Vegas?! ANY GIVEN SUNDAY BABY!). It was the second game of a double header for both teams so the score was low but Power Yellow fapped just a little bit harder towards the end to earn the money shot. Let's see if they can start another win streak straight to the DCGFFL Season X championship trophy.
results_10_comment: “Surrender Dorothy.” That from  Camo QB Mark H and Captain Kody S as they steamrolled over Purple. “I’ll get you my little pretty.” Using a bag of tricks that looked like plays borrowed from Purple team JJ’s  plays from a previous season, he executed over and over leaving Purple in a field of poppies, asleep.  Mark went to the usual cast of characters as he found love with receivers Matt M and Cole W over and over. Can we keep Cole off the injured list? He landed on the field as if dropped by a tornado… and returned in his ruby red slippers and Toto too. “Throw a bucket of water on that witch” from the Purple Captain Raul. The Plum Dumpsters were stuck in Kansas as Camo marched down the Yellow Brick Road all the way to the Emerald City. Flying Monkey Ali flew in for a TD followed by Brian H for another. But Good Witch of the North Mark H had too many spells. He spread the magic to Amanda L for a TD and an XP to Daniel H. Nick S mounted his broom and flew in for a sack for Dumpsters. “Take that Glenda.”  The End. Movie over. Turn up the lights.
results_11_comment: No one was singing Ebony and Ivory in perfect harmony as each team was writing its own battle cries. Black QB Nathan F sang love songs to Rudy when they put up TD’s. Nathan started with “I’m a little bit country, you’re a little bit rock-n-roll.” White team QB Marvin impressed with “Busta Move” as he scored a TD, XP and another TD. “Can’t Touch This.” Captain Adam S sang an incoherent Jewish folk song . The translation was clear: “I sacked the QB.” Black Captain was not to be outdone as he pulled out margaritas, a guitar, and a sombrero for the Mexican Bean Dance. White Captain put the pressure on with more rushing. Black was rattled.  More music played as White sang up and down the register with TD dances to Josh K and Adam S. Jim R’s coda was an XP (while solidly playing all game.) Black turned up the music. “I can name that tune in one INT” from Patrick M. It was a sing-off show down. But Black just couldn’t finish the song. White Team won this Talent Show.
results_12_comment: Midas must have (inappropriately) touched every one of these men because the whole team is SOLID gold! The team didn't skip a beat without QB Sheerod (out with a broken leg). Newcomer Brian S joins the elite list of best QB understudies which include legends like Kyle B and Adam R. Now if only someone can get him a pair of shorts that don't clash with his gold jersey. In other gold news, newcomer Will L finally got to meet his predecessor Scott S at Nellies and the world is wondering if they are long lost twins. Red ultimately finished the day 0-2 and only have one week to turn things around before the playoffs!

results_3_mvp: George G. (Power Yellow), Jamar W. (Vegas Gold)
results_0_comment: On a night when Lime was missing some of its star power, starting the game with only 7 players, the Legion of Doom took advantage and triumphed 37-20 under the lights.  BB and Josh R. each had 2 tds and Jim R. and James D. added in 1 of their own in White's victory.  Lime's TDs came from Smiffy, Captain Brian G. and Shawn N.  John R. had 2 sacks in the victory.  He proclaimed afterwards, "I'm the sack king of Friday F'ing Night!"
results_1_comment: Was it strategic that Fuschia jerseys were hard to miss on this Friday Night Lights game?  Glowing under the lights, QB Tyler was able to spread the ball around—one for you and one for you and one for you—to Andy L, Austin, and Trey. Trey showcasing his catching skills, dashed in and out of traffic as he moved the ball downfield.  Red Hot Thots weren’t quite lukewarm in this forgettable first half. Lauren P showed up to play and added two sacks to her rushing stats. But it wasn’t enough pressure to even the game. Red team rusher Ken G added some sacks 1-2-3 to his goody bag and earned MVP with his constant pressure.  By the half this game, it was clear: Fuschia was too bright for Red.
results_2_comment: Royal exploded on FNL for 52 offensive points, winning by 46 over the Teal squad missing a few players.  QB Matt P. caught an INT for Royal on Teal's first offensive play of the game and the rout was on.  Just about everyone who played offense for the Royal squad had a TD - Miles S. (x 3), Linda P. (x 2), Peter S. (x 2), and Jason B. (x 1).  Peter D. had Teal's lone score.  After the game Royal Captain Moptop was pissed that he didn't score a TD, threatening to bench his QB the next time that happened.
results_3_comment: In a let down of an offensive game, Royal was unable to match its 52 point FNL output just two days prior, scoring only 46 in this one.  Moptop thankfully didn't have to bench QB Matt P. because he caught Royal's final TD of the weekend.  Peter S (x 2), Clev, Robert B. and Miles S. added the other scores for Royal.   Josh S. had Maroon's lone score; he also added in a sack as did Diggy.  Welcome back Diggy!  Derek J. added in 2 sacks of his own for Royal and Cody B. added in a black eye.  He feels butch now.
results_4_comment: They may be Silver but they’re playing for gold.  Silver QB John B maintained his edge and crazy audible system that produces results. Nolan L. came out of nowhere over and over and shined like silver bling. Pulling down INTs and tipped balls—4 in all-- he’s a player to watch. Purple, handicapped with a sitting QB (Craig N) for the first half, an injured Howard Y, Brion out for the season, and Ali on a questionable mission elsewhere proved too harmful for Purple to make a respectable showing.  For Silver, little known Andy S was the secret weapon sneaking in 3 TD/s. John B spread silver coins—and love--  to newbie Walt S and Ken G. Ken G, loud and in full glory, managed to plow over a Purple player. But hey, who cares when you’re winning.  A blow out for Silver. Kevin who?
results_5_comment: Without primary QB, Navy used team darling Daniel H as QB and he succeeded in spreading his warn-n-fuzzy love to Captain Greg K, Levert, and new-to-the league-but-not-to football Mike C. Touchdowns all in first half. For Teal, QB Peter D found his way to the end zone. Touchdown. XP to Chris R.  Tealer Tim S pulled down an INT and then put 6 on the board in the second half. But Navy had this game wrapped. Newbies to the league, Noah and Chris M put their pressure and speed to use. Each pulling down a sack. Barry M showed his vintage talent with a TD and Levert followed suit. Mike C add the XP.
results_6_mvp: Bill C. (Dark Green), Josh E. (Sky Blue)
results_6_comment: In a game featuring the bottom two power ranked squads, Burnt Orange showed there was considerable distance between 19th and 20th, winning 36-20.  Burton, Jake C. Sam S. (x 2) and Mike Z. gathered TDs for the BO team. Diggy, Charlie and Andy A. scored for Maroon.  Adam R. made his season debut for QB in the second half of this one.  Meredith and Mike Z had INTs for BO with Mike Z's being a pick 6.  Who knew that girl had some speed?!  Congrats BO.
results_7_comment: An anticipated game for these two teams determined to take a another W to its column. Without its starting QB for the first half, Alex P stepped up for his best song and dance.  But he couldn’t choreograph any good moves. Heather Slate took advantage of this lopsided first half by spreading the ball everywhere and fortifying its efforts. QB Kyle spread love to Andy P, Gabe A, and Bo. As defender Kyle M proved why it’s a bad idea to throw anywhere near his side of the field. INT for him.  Sequoia didn’t disappoint with her sack. But wait this game isn’t over. Enter Black QB Nathan and we have a new game. He used Alex P like a fleshlight, firing one shot after another. A TD and XP to Alex P gave new life to Black. Followed by a TD to Patrick M and Jacob, Nathan proved he’s a QB to watch.  Matt P, up to his usual tricks, snagged another sack. The second half battle was respectable for Black, but not enough to win.
results_8_comment: A game matching up the #1 ranked team in undefeated Gold and the #4 team in Power Blue turned out to be a game worth watching, as the Blue Collar Twerkers ran out the clock to win in this low scoring battle 19-13.  Gold was hampered by QB Sheerod W.'s first half ankle sprain on a long run from scrimmage.  He stayed in at QB but was unable to move and thus couldn't play defense.  The game was 7-7 at the half with both teams driving each time they had the ball but with Gold's second possession ending in a goalline INT and Blue's second possession ending as time expired at the goal.  In the second half Blue's defense didn't give up a score until the final 2 minutes.  Porter and Bryan S. had Gold's TDs while Larry W. (x2) and Jerrell had Power Blue's TDs with Larry, Marcus and Jerrell each adding an INT.  Mike H. was MVP for the chain moving catches he had throughout the game as undefeated Gold fell to Power Blue.
results_9_comment: An anticipated game between two strong armies, Navy and Camo went to war. The Battle Of Waterloo ensued as Navy Team put in QB Napolean Daniel H as stand-in general. Across enemy line was Goliath Mark H as opposing QB for Camo Grey.  Hard to disguise under that camo, he commandeered a strong first half. QB Mark scored and then spread the military might to Matt M and Cole W for TD’s.  Amanda L pulled down the catch of her career under full coverage.  “Where’s my war glory? You gays aren’t the only bitches in town. Move over.”  Refusing to give up ground, Napolean QB Daniel shared strategic intel   with Levert  and he marched to a TD. Mike C encroached further with an XP. But at half Camo Grey was winning the battle. With renewed effort in the second half of this war, Navy came out with new war plans, new strategies, artillery, and F-Bombs.  Advancing their campaign, Navy’s war chest included TDs by Chris M and Napolean himself.  But Camo was having none of it. Secret weapon Vikas—dusted off the sideline shelf—made stealthy moves to a TD. Camo waged its war with star soldiers Cole W, Matt M, and Braeden. Mark H pulled down a long range missile when he yanked down an INT.  With Napolean sidelined for violating International Terms of DCGFFL War, Chris M filled in as QB and managed to connect with fellow soldier Mike C for another TD. “You gays aren’t the only ones who get to dress up in pretty military outfits. I like a man in uniform too.” That from Chris M.  But Camo won this Battle of the Bulge.
results_10_comment: Dark Green found some love this weekend.  QB Bill C, back from some unknown vacation to nowhere, decided to prove he still has what it takes. “I can still shake my hips and dance down the field. Just watch.” He connected with Peter and Yama for a meh first half, but now 12 points on the board. But two sacks by Kyle energized the team.  Steve G seemed to be Sky Blue’s only threat as he spring-rolled for a TD, INT, and XP.  Second half offered more dynamic events. Ryan S for Dark Green said, “Aw Shucks” as he put points on the board. Jack M racked up stats with an INT and an XP. Bill C added another INT to the mix. Sky Blue found other teammates in the second half when Josh E and Adam S supported the teams efforts: TDs for each. But Dark Green had too much for these Sky Blue boys.
results_11_comment: Power Yellow pulled off an improbable win over the #2 ranked Vegas Gold squad despite missing 3 of their stars (Simeon, Bryant and Marlon) who were off dilly dallying around Africa, California and elsewhere.  Power Yellow's supplemental picks Joe and Brandon led the way, as Joe reeled in 2 TDS and Brandon caught an INT in the victory, 25-18.  QB George G. caught 2 INTs as well and Captain Sean S. had a TD of his own.  Jason W., Jamar W. and Keith C. had Vegas's TDs in the loss.  Of note, Jamar had this ridiculous one-handed catch behind his body on a slant pass.  Javi was nervous he threw his back out making it.

results_0_comment: In a game overslept by Doom's Brandon B., the White team took advantage of a 0 point output by the Rangers in the first half to win this one by 12.  Kip M., Captain Strasberg, Allison K. and John R. all recorded sacks on Cammas in the 1st half.  The turning point of the game, however, was with White leading 6-0 with the Rangers 5 yards away from a tying score when Doomer Jim R. stepped in front of a pass and took it to the house for a pick 6.  Jim R. would add another TD in the second half as would Josh R.  Dark Green came alive in the second half with TDs from Shealy and Yama, but too little too late, as White wins 26-14.
results_1_comment: The Liminators rode a first half pick 6 at their own goalline by Dameron R. to victory, winning by 18.  Turnt QB Jim C. trying to rush because he thought he saw an opening, threw a pass towards Burton but Dameron stepped in front and scampered down the sideline for the score.  He would add another INT and TD later in the game.  Jarod T. captured 13 points for the Teal squad.  Turnt gathered in 3 INTs in the loss - Burton, newcomer Cameron and Sweeney all had a takeaway, while Z, Jake C. and Burton had Burnt Orange's scores.
results_2_comment: The Mooners used a 25 point 1st half to give the Royal team the Blues, winning 38-29 in this contest.  Tyler E. had a pick 6 and a rushing TD in the first half for Navy and Daniel H. also added a 1st half score.  Of particular note, DCGFFL Board member Sam B. scored his first league TD, as Navy had it going on.  Jason C., Miles S. (x 2) and QB Matt P. added scores for the Varsity Blues and MVP Linda P. kept the chains moving down the field in the loss, 38-29.
results_3_comment: The Thots roared out to an early lead with two scores by Scott K. and Alonzo M. and defensive stop.  Thanks to a TV timeout, the SkySexuals cut the lead to 8 with a TD at end of first half by Captain Kyle B.  Josh E. (sky blue) and Cody G. (red) also scored in the first half.  Gerard B. "changed the game" with a pick-6 early in 2nd half, leading to a back and forth game with 2 lead changes in final 2 minutes.  Sky captain Kyle B. said, "Hats off to Earl/Red for their impressive game winning drive with 45 seconds left," as Long D.'s final TD proved to be the winner, 33-28.
results_4_comment: In a game that was supposed to be played under the lights on Friday night, Camo didn't need the lights to shine bright in this one, winning by 21.  As the Spooners Captain Joe H. stated, "silver's defense couldn't stop camo's qb from finding whatever receiver he wanted," as Braden (td), Tackney (xp), Amanda (td), Matt M. (xp, 2tds), Cole (td & xp), Andrew C. (xp) and Hofberg (2tds) got in on the scoring for Camo.  Silver's TDs were thanks to QB John B., Kevin K., Nolan L. and Ken G.
results_5_comment: Power Yellow came out to play on Sunday. A bedazzled first half put Power Yellow firmly in control—and looking pretty—with the usual suspects putting TD’s on the board. QB George raked up another and Bryant B answered with “I won’t be topped, er, on points.” Give him 2 TD’s. There was a collective sideline eye-roll when Matt S yanked down an INT. “Oh brother. That one again?” Maroon, missing starters for both O and D, tried their darnedest to maintain dignity. Andy A reached for the stars on a deep-ball catch in close one-on-one coverage.  With ball in hand he added yards—and bling—to the play. Captain Adam scored a long TD from a block-n-release with Power Yellow Matt S and George G in pursuit. “Nyah nyah nyah” from Adam when putting up the points. Just as the Humane Society arrived to put Maroon kittens out of their misery, they rebounded with a respectable second half. INT’s from Paul and Will helped their cause. Andy A added hope to the litter with a TD. First career TD for Josh S came from a pitch up the middle.  Fortifying the defensive efforts, Michelle F and supplemental addition Scott T yanked flags off of shifty-hips Matt S. Tony S added another INT to his day for Power Yellow. A valiant effort out Maroon still leaves them winless and QB Charlie on suicide watch. But don’t kick these kittens…they’re eating Meow Mix and getting ready for the next ball of yarn.
results_6_comment: A game that was solidly in the Twerkers column for most of it, even being up 24-6 in the second half; but the Mean Mother Fuchsias never stopped clawing and fought back to put pressure on the Twerkers late in the game, losing only by 6, 31-25.  Newcomer Austin P. was dominating in every facet of the game, making circus catches, including an INT and a TD.  QB Tyler L. ran 2 TDs in and Trey P. had Fuchsia's other TD.  Larry W. had 2 TDs for Power Blue, while Marcus, Adam B. and Bornmann each added 1.  Marcus and QB Brandon had INTs on defense in the win.
results_7_comment: Refs showed up to officiate this hockey game turned fight. Out of the box, Vegas Gold drove down the field swiftly and scored with QB connecting to Jason W and XP to Jamar. Working with a lean crew, Purple took possession for as long as it takes Craig N to drop his pants and swiftly surrendered the ball when quiet storm Jared L snagged an INT for Vegas near the red zone and ran in for a Pick Six. The game managed to get noisy despite the fact that Ali was nowhere to found—NSA Alert—as this Romper Room game got uglier and uglier. Purple regained hope as Howard Y snagged his own INT. A steady battle ensued and QB Craig connected with Brion for a TD. All players came out of their corners and put on their Romper Stompers and marched to field for more fighting. Refs, frustrated and angry with the madness of the game, made stern warnings about the chirpiness and the aggressive nature of the game. Through his Romper Room Magic Mirror, Ref Paddy Mac, said, “Craig N and Chris M and all you bad boys, settle down. Play time is too rough.” Shortly thereafter Craig N  flying down the field creating a sonic boom, pitches the ball back to teammate Brion, and then does his best freight train collision with Vegas Gold Chris M. That’s a wall, not a tunnel. Ejected for 8 plays. Both teams warned. Again. Continuing its policy of only using players whose names begin with J, Vegas Gold banked on Jamar for 2 more TDs and Jared L had an XP. Jason W didn’t look far for an INT thrown directly to him. Purple, unable to play the game they wanted, sang B-I-NGO and Bingo was his name-o under the direction of Ref Paddy M. Second half scoring by QB Craig and, and redeeming himself, added to his stats 2 INTs and a stirring version of Ol’ MacDonald Had a Farm.  Kindergarten class adjourned for both teams.
results_8_comment: The Enemies expanded on a 1 point halftime lead to win by 9 points, 27-18 in this one.  Judson, newly-married Gabe A., Captain Kozak and newcomer Bo B. had Slate's scores.  And Sequoia H. added to her sack total with another sack.  Rob C. scored two TDs for the Lime team while Sam C. had 1 TD and 1 INT in the loss.
results_9_comment: This game was dominated by the Thots from start to finish, with Long D. catching an INT on the opening drive then scoring 2 plays into his first drive, as Red never trailed winning 39-20.  Pretty much the whole Thots Squad got in on the scoring as Cody G. (xp), Scott K. (td), QB Earl A. (td), Mecha s. (sack), Alonzo (2tds, xp, pick 6), Brett C. (xp) and Elon (td) all made huge contributions as did David B. for putting pressure on the opposing QB.  The Twerkers were twerked out from the first game but Marcus B. did have a huge offensive game, scoring 19 of Power Blue's 20 points in the loss.
results_10_comment: Continuing the Romper Room shenanigans, Power Yellow showed up for their play-date with Purple and a new crew of chaperons, er, refs.  Each team screamed and clawed and fussed in this intense match that finished with a victory—and a sippy cup drink-- for Power Yellow. Intense and fast moving, this game showcased more O than D.  Power Yellow Captain Sean Stern started the show with a TD. Power Yellow QB spread the ball around and scrambled and rolled. Cashing in big plays were Marlon D and Bryant B for TD’s. Matt S, checked off another INT on his to-do list. George G had to sit in the corner for his wet-britches meltdown. “Don’t come back till you change your Pull-Ups and your attitude, young man” from Ref Greg K. Down to three plays in the half, Brion, for Purple, runs the ball all the way to the candy store from Purple’s own 2 yard line. With only one play remaining, Power Yellow says “I want some Jolly Ranchers too!” QB George G—wearing fresh Pull-Ups—rushes downfield, does a crazy, cross-field lateral to Bryant B who takes it all the way to Sugar Shop. Purple QB did what he could do with a lean Purple roster.  Howard Y on the sideline for injury, Purple was unable to keep up. Second half, Brion added a QB and Craig N found another INT. Power Y Tony S, on the receiving end of things this season, added a TD to his illustrious career. Joe C helped Power Yellow with an INT. Marlon D was steady throughout the game with TD and XP. Bryant B got his mouth washed out with soap for using big-boy words to the Refs.

results_4_mvp: Matt M. (Camo Grey) Mike Z. (Burnt Orange)
results_0_comment: The Mooners trailed 19-7 at the half but said they'd showed enough of their butts and turned it around in the second half almost completing the comeback, as the Spooners took the victory by 5.  The Blue Mooners got behind early before mounting a strong comeback effort in the second half, but ultimately the Silver Spooners emerged victorious by a final score of 27-22.  Navy's MVP QB Tyler E powered his way to 2 rush TDs and passed to a wide-open Honeycutt for a third, while Barry M secured a couple XPs in heavy traffic. Silver Spooner Andrew M hauled in three TDs from quarterback J.B., while clutch 3rd down and late-game receptions by MVP Nolan L sealed the deal. Spooner Kevin K made the game's only interception.
results_1_comment: With Superbowl runner-up QB Sheerod W. out of town, it looked as though Gold's unbeaten season would come to an end.  "Not so fast my friend," proclaimed Lee Corso as he put on a mask of the Midas Man.  The Gold team, under the direction of newcomer and backup QB (and grinder as the author would later learn at Nellie's) Bryan S., the Touchdowns slowed down none, putting up 32 points and winning by 20.  Newcomers littered the heck out of Gold's scoresheet with John accounting for 18 points and William L. for 7 points.  Andy P. had both of Slate's scores in the loss.
results_2_comment: Too afraid to show up, QB Matt P. left his team at the altar in this match. Royal captain Jason C took on the job. “Matt may be a better QB but I get more tail.”   Purple dominated first half with TD’s from pretty Beiber Hotch and—spoiler alert!—Brion. And then Brion scored again. Hotch and QB Craig pulled down INT’s in first half. Neiswanger got a speeding ticket on his return. Royal was having coffee in the first half but sent in a rusher who snagged a sack. “These croissants are delicious” said Captain Mop. “You gays have taught me how to appreciate the finer things in life. Pass the mimosa, please.” Coffee kicked in for Royal and they showed up in second half with impressive playing and putting up 20 points. TD’s to Captain Moptop, and Peter S. Fill-in QB Jason C ran like a feral kitty for another. “I thought we had a real, straight threeway bromance” said Moptop about QB Matt P and Peter S…”But no.”
results_3_comment: This defensive struggle, which saw an INT returned on an XP conversion, another INT at the goal and a goal line stand, saw the Klingons run the clock out and beat the previously-unbeaten Twerkers by 4 points.  Marcus B. had 2 INTs, one that he ran back for the Power Blue team's only first half points off an XP conversion.  Larry W. and Captain Jerrell P. had the scores for the Twerkers.  Smiffy scored Lime's first half TD, while newcomer Michelle T. added 2 TDs in the second half, the second proving to be the game-winner on a great grab streaking across the back of the endzone on a 4th down.  Jeremy S. had a game-changing INT at the goal line for Lime, as Lime wins 19-15.
results_4_comment: A busy first half in this game came down to a tie of 7 all as each team slugged it out on O and D. Burnt Orange scored with Jake C doing his slippery routine for an extra point. Mike Z with a sack, but not wig, demanded to be noticed. Camo Grey showed its deep roster of talent with Pretty Boy Matt M. bringing down a TD and an INT. Not to be upstaged Cole W. pulled down an extra point and an INT and followed with “Hey, I’m pretty too.” Another TD in the second half for Matt M settled the dispute. “I’m prettier.” Braeden B. and Captain Kody hushed Drag Queen Mike Z when each pulled down sacks. The game rallied with Camo Grey on top, er.
results_5_comment: The Faps dominated the Mooners, winning by 20 in this one.  Enrique "el jefe" started the scoring off with a nice TD, giving the Faps a 6-0 lead.  QB George G. ran the next score in and Marlon D. had a nice back-of-the-endzone catch and an XP to give Power Yellow a 20-0 lead.  Supplemental pick Joe C. added the Faps' final score of the half, to carry a 26-0 lead into the break.  The second half was all Navy as they won the half 6-0.  Supplemental pick Daniel H. had a second half INT as did Tyler E. for Navy, while QB Tyler E. ran in the Mooners lone score in the loss 26-6.
results_6_comment: Borderline straights—Andy P. and Cody G.—one from each team,  came out to play in this sure-n-steady game. Supplemental straight draft pick for Red Team,  Mecha  followed with “Hey I’m straight and I’m a girl. A real girl.”  Heather Slate Captain managed to pull down a TD in the first half without a call to 911. Andy Pratt followed with a TD. Gabe A., in pre-wedding bliss, pulled down an INT.  From the Red team, Alonzo snagged an INT and Brett C. put 6 on the board.  For Slate, Andy P. continued to impress with great catches and an INT . Judson pulled down a TD. QB Kyle has sure-bet receivers on this Slate Team. For Red, Cody G. made his QB shine with a TD. QB Earl ran in for an extra point.
results_7_comment: The Rangers finally found the right side of the win column despite QB Bill C. throwing 2 INTs in this one.  After the game I caught up with Bill C.  Here's his quote, "I'm the worst QB in the league; I have no idea how my team won this game.  Is there a supplemental QB they can draft."  Uh huh, he really said that, riiiiight. ;)  Anyway, Black struggled to find its offense without its starting QB, scoring only 13 points in this contest on TDs by Billy and Pesesky.  The Rangers scores came at the hands of Yama (2, one a Pick 6), Shealy, and Peter P.
results_8_comment: Sky Blue is looking upward. In a close game, Sky Blue went stratospheric on Sunday with two wins on a hard-played double-header day.  Sky Blue Captain Kyle B. kept his feet on the ground on Sunday as he coached and played his team to a turnaround that no-one expected. Kyle put 3 TD’s on the board and QB Adam rushed in for a fourth. Lime rallied with solid performance by various players including an INT by Captain Brian G. Dennis M. put up a TD in the first half followed by Michele with an extra point.  Jeremy S., up to his old tricks, continued to make Lime relevant with a strong performance on D. INT in first half and converted with a safety slowing the Sky Blue march. Second half,  Lime continued with Jeremy S counting up another TD while QB Dan rushed in—no walker on this guy-- for one of his own. “Gurl, you know I got that extra point, right?” and then he double-snapped….that’s our Smiffy.
results_9_comment: According to Teal, this game was determined by the sober refs. “When did JJ sober up? He’s a better ref when he’s drunk” came from loudest man in the league Dameron. “@#$%@! Ref and #$%@!#!% Ref” from fellow Teal teammate Jared T.  Working with a 2-man crew, refs did their best to keep up with a fast paced game.  Each team battled for dominance and proved its mettle. Vegas Gold looks good on Jared L. and Jamar. Both scored in first half and Jared L added an extra point. Teal QB Peter D. was having none of the It-Stays-In Vegas mantra. Plucking an INT in the first half and driving down fields and resulting in touchdowns to Charlie K. and Jared T. At half: Vegas 14. Teal 12. The battle continues in the second half.  Big Bird Scott G in all his feathers, leaps and flies, and oh, wait, there’s a sack—and a snap over his head-- on Teal QB. He also rushes in for a QB. Teal Captain Jayme led by example by putting up six and QB Peter too. Vegas Gold Keith C. made his team proud pulling down one crazy play after another. Jared T. on Teal was his usual Top Shelf performer. “No ma’am, I will not be ignored” was Dameron’s response delivering another big game.
results_10_comment: A 1 point game at the half quickly got out of hand for the Maroons Over My Hammy who apparently packed it up early to get the Early Bird special at Denny's (see what i did there??!).  The Camo Toes scored the final 33 points of this contest, thanks to 4 INTs, 2 by Cole and 1 a piece by Charlie S. and Hofberg.  Camo's TDs were thanks to 2 TDs by Cole, 1 TD by Andrew C. and 2 runs by Hofberg for scores. Maroon's lone score was by PeePaw.
results_11_comment: Playing as substitute QB, Tyler F wowed. “Dude, it’s like rocky mountain high, but we’re, like, dude, in DC aren’t we?” Connecting again and again with Will J., they collected TD’s like STD’s. Trey P. impressed with a TD, extra point and a sack. Throwing the qb’s flag like it were shade, he said “Pink is my color b****.”  Marvin pulled down 2 INTs in first half and connected with Jim R for a TD.  White continued fighting as James counted two sacks. Josh R. got an INT. Fuschia kept up the fight, defensively, in the second half with Tyler F pulling down two INT’s, lucky stars, moons, and unicorns, dude. Ken G said “aw shucks” when he got a sack.  Fuschia was just too bright for white.
results_12_comment: Has Sky Blue been hustling us all along? Bruised, black and blue, Sky Blue crushed on Black.  Does it take a supplemental pick Gerard to make this happen?  Not so fast. Sky Blue made use of players like one-night-stands. That one, that one, and that one. TD’s to newbie Jeremy K. (“Hey mom I play with gays.”) and supplemental star Gerard (“Hey mom, I am that gay.”) followed by extra points to Josh E. Everyone yawned with Billy K. scored another touchdown for Black.  Second half was like putting out fire with gasoline as Sky Blue poured it on. Josh E, Gerard and Jeremy K (Pick Six thankyouverymuch) made up for a less than stellar start of season.  Asian Inspiration Steve G contributed with and extra point and solid samarai sword swinging.  Rudy filled in as Q on black but couldn’t get points on the board. Ricky M yanked a sack for Black. Don’t be afraid of the gay, Nathan F… Black needs you.

results_2_mvp: Mark H. (Camo Grey); Enrique P. (Power Yellow
results_0_comment: A first half battle between these strong teams left this game tied at the half.  Black was playing   without its QB but Rudy B. stepped in for a solid performance.  Cody G., Alonzo and Brett pulled   down INT’s for Red. Patrick M. answered with an INT for Black. Matty P. maintained her rushing   might with a sack.  Alex P crushed with catches, a TD and 2-point conversion.
results_1_comment: A very windy day didn't prevent an excellent overtime game with incredible defensive plays, a last minute tying drive and an OT INT.  The Legion of Doom picked off Twerker QB Brandon W. twice (Jim R. and Marvin W.) but were unable to hold off Marcus B. and the Twerkers game-tying drive with less than a minute to go, as the Twerkers scored the TD and Captain Jerrell added the tying 2 point conversion on a broken down play to force overtime.  In the OT, Captain Jerrell P. again made a huge play, picking QB Marvin W. off for the 4th time on the first play of OT.  Marcus B. had a pick 6 in the victory, as the Twerkers doom the Doom 26-20.
results_2_comment: A neck-n-neck game by two teams fighting for a respect.  Power Yellow blocking wasn’ t, um,   powerful enough to ward off two sacks from Camo Grey Captain Kody S. and Braden B. Power   Yellow captain Sean S. answered with a sack of his own. Power Yellow QB showed a more   varied game than previous seasons. Two TD’s to Enrique and another to genie-out-of-the-bottle   Matt S. put 18 points on the board for Power Faps. (What’s this team name?!) Camo Grey had   strong showing by Cole. W and Matt M. INT by Mark H. shocks—JUST SHOCKS!—everyone.
results_3_comment: A dynamic Purple team proved too much for Teal. In first half, TD successes were spread among   Howard Y., Clay A., and Brion. QB Craig rushed in for another TD.  Howard and Brion pulled   down INT’s. Greg K rattled QB Peter D with a sack. Craig N. was the answer to Dameron’s usual   strong performance. Teal had big performances out of center Jared T. He impressed with   blocking and crazy-impressive 1-handed catch for an extra point conversion. TJ R. put 6 on the   board for Teal in first half. QB Peter D. rushed in for a TD.
results_4_comment: Scoreboard didn’t reflect the strong performance out of Sky Blue for 3/4s of the game. Sky Blue   enjoyed an improved performance—and points on the board—by QB Adam M.  QB’s connected   with Captain Kyle B., Eduardo C., and AJ D. AJ showed impressive catching and running. On D,   Sky Blue couldn’t be ignored. INT’s by Josh E. and Matt G. On Fuschia, Ken F demanded to be   taken seriously. He pulled down an extra point conversion, a Pick Six and  yet another TD.   Fuschia QB Tyler L. –looking fabulous in shocking pink and ripped shorts—spread the ball   around and found Andy L. as a wily teammate with 2 TD’s in the first half. QB Tyler L. has   showcased his well-rounded team. Sky Blue Steve Gong reached for the, er, sky with an   impressive 3 ½” vertical to catch a big play in the middle. He was a reliable go to with smart   routes and good catches.
results_5_comment: A solid battle between two good teams, as backup QB Rudy L-B not only kept his team in this one, putting up 24 points.  He threw TD passes to Billy K., Alex P., Patrick M. and Captain Adrian M.  The two stars for the Twerkers were Captain Jerrell P., who gathered in 4 TDs (including one that Head Ref PMac said reminded him of Odell Beckham's TD) and 1 INT and Mike H., who had 2 INTs and 1 XP in the game.  The Twerkers win 32-24.
results_6_comment: The Midas Touchdowns proved again that they’ve got the touch. Captain Randy S. outwitted  everyone when he drafted league rookies who know how to play gold-touch football. Sheerod   W. continues his strong performance as QB. New players Bryan S. and John C. proved size   doesn’t matter when each made bigger-than-themselves performances. INT’s and TD’s by both.   D. Mitch wasn’t to be ignored on D with 2 INT’s. Lime team QB Dan C. highlighted the talents of   new women’s player Michele T. when she put up a 1st half TD. QB Dan scored another TD and   Rob C. pulled in the extra point.  Rob C. made impressive showing on D.
results_7_comment: Royal put their undefeated record on the line versus steam-gaining Silver in this close battle.  Captain Brendan M. and Miles S. split all 4 of the Blues scores while Nolan L. caught 2 TDs and Kevin K. gathered in the other one as Silver came up just short 24-18.  Royals Derrick had 2 sacks in the win.
results_8_comment: Put your money on Vegas Gold.  Chris M.’s Vegas Gold dominated this game with a show-me-the-money   performance. QB Scott G. spread the ball around and favoring anyone who’s first name starts with a J:    Jamar, Jason  W., Jared L. all cashed in on TD’s. Jason W. wants Vegas Showgirl attention with strong   showing on D and brought down an INT with feathers in her uniform. Emory R. added to the pile with a   TD. JP did his job as rusher and tallied a sack.  Maroon couldn’t recover from numerous INT’s.  Working   out the kinks on O, there weren’t enough  connections to put points on the board. Andy A. and Will C.   impressed on D with INT’s.
results_9_comment: This was a tale of two halves as Slate looked dominant in the first half taking a 14-0 lead off scores by QB Kyle M. and Andy P. with XPs by Bo B. and Captain Kozak.  But the SkySexuals decided to 'vers it up in the second half, roaring back on TDs by Matt G. and QB Adam M.  Captain Kyle B. had Sky's lone XP and Gong had his first (ever?) INT in the loss 14-13.
results_10_comment: Gold looked dominant once again, proving that they belong near the top of the Power Rankings in this rematch of Season 9's Superbowl QBs.  "Revenge is sweet," said Gold's QB Sheerod W. (or did I just make up that quote?).  Sheerod threw 2 TDs each to newcomers Bryan S. and John C. with DMitch grabbing the other one.  John C. also added in 2 INTs in the game.  The Rangers  had two scores from newcomer Peter P. and 1 from Nix in the loss, 34-19.
results_11_comment: Lime was up 14-13 at the half but down with less than a minute to go with Smiffy rescued the Klingons from the Mean Mother Fuchsias on a last second TD to win 26-21.  Trey P. (aka LuLu), Ken O. and Tyler L. all had TDs and Tyler L. caught 2 INTs in the loss.  Smiffy had 19 of Lime's 26 points, with Jeremy S. adding in the other TD and Captain Brian G. grabbing an XP.  Lulu could be heard cursing at the sky at the end of this one because he's a Mean Mother FU....
results_12_comment: It was a battle of wills and grit and noisy players.  Neither team would surrender in this back-n-forth   duel. Silver team QB barked indecipherable audibles that made sense to Kevin K. as he played with a   dynamic force and showed his connection with his QB. Andrew M. was the first to put points on the   board for Silver. Ken G.—in full volume and full control—snagged catch after catch and racked up two   TD’s and two conversions. Nolan L. wasn’t to be ignored as he put up a TD hoping the refs wouldn’t   notice his flagrant pass interference later.  He thought it was ok to chase a player down the field like he   chases his tricks. The rule is the same: Look for the balls. Burnt Orange put newly-returned John B. to   work as if it were the ol’ days. They connected on short routes and steadily moved the ball. Burnt   Orange Captain Marcus pulled down a TD. QB Jim found an ally in Jake C. who knows how to make his   QB shine and put two TD’s on the board while slipping through the defense as if he was lubed up head   to toe rushing long yards on the way to the end zone.  QB JTrain beat Ken G in the Decibel Dept when   shouting at refs.
results_13_comment: If you were on Navy and you didn't collect an INT in this one, you must literally have been Mooning the Hammies during each play.  Levert, Barry M., and Captain Greg K. all had an INT and newcomer Mike C. grabbed 2 of his own in victory over the Maroon squad.  Oh by the way, Mike C. added 4 TDs as well.  Captain AdRob added an INT of his own and Diggy grabbed two in the loss for Maroon with Will and Brian D. scoring TDs for Maroon in the loss 25-12.

results_0_comment: The Legion of Doom started Season X off by living up to their name, blanking the SkySexuals.  Marvin W. spread the ball around efficiently, throwing TDs to Captain Adam S., BB, Robert M and 2 to newcomer James D, while running two more in.  New QB Adam M. and the rest of the SkySexuals got off to a shaky Season X start but thankfully they don't have to play the Legion of Doom's defense every week!
results_1_comment: The Turnt Orange squad squeaked out a 4 point victory and sent the Yellow squad home in time for a Power Fap (see what I did there?).  Jake C. had a strong day with 2 TDs for the Burnt Orange team, while the league officially welcomed John B. back from San Diego.  He had a TD and 2 XPs to collect the MVP for the Turnts.  Bryant B. and Simeon split 4 TDs while Marlon D. surprisingly showed up without perfect conditions and collected an INT in the loss.  Turnt Orange 32-28.
results_2_comment: New QB Nathan gathered in his first victory in the league, putting up 26 points and winning by two scores.  Fuchsia's scorecard was a mirror image of itself from the two halves - Tyler F. had a TD while Tyler L. had an INT and Ken G. had a sack all in the first half.  In the second half Tyler F. got the INT, Tyler L. got the TD and Ken G. collected his second sack.  The BNO team had strong production from Jacob W. as he scored 3 TDs; Captain Adrian M. had the other TD and Rudy added a second half INT.
results_3_comment: This game came down to who had possession last, as 0 stops were made on either side, the Dark Green Rangers simply ran out of time and the Thots held on for a 4 point advantage and a 1-0 record.  Red QB Earl A. looked back to form after being out a season with an ACL injury.  He threw 5 tds on the day - 2 to Captain Nikki, and one a piece to Long D., Brett C. and Cody G.  Meanwhile, Shealy dominated on offense for the Rangers, accounting for 19 of their 26 points in the loss.
results_4_comment: Season 9 Superbowl runner up QB Sheerod continued his dominating ways, throwing 5 TDs and converting on all 5 XPs against the previously unscored upon Legion of Doom.  DMitch scored twice, while Porter, Bryan and Sheerod accounted for the other 3 scores in the victory.  White got production from Josh R., Marvin and Allison with Kip M. grabbing a pick 6 in the loss.
results_5_comment: League veteran turned first time Captain MopTop was victorious behind an always reliable Matt P. Turnt Orange made it interesting with scores from John B. Sam S. and Meridith B. but ran out of steam in their second matchup of the day.
results_6_comment: Jayme F. and Peter D. kicked-off Teal's season in the right direction by easily handling a Captain-less Maroon team. Last seasons MVP Dameron R. picked up right where he left off and Peter D. looked sharp in his return to field general. Let's see if Maroon will fare better with Adam R. back next week.
results_7_comment: It's not quite St Patty's day yet but the showdown of the Greens was an exciting event! Kevin S. and Lime squeezed out a win over the Dark Green Rangers. Peter P. takes home this weeks game MVP honors for his team, but no W's. How can a Bill C. led team be 0-2? Anything can happen in Season X!
results_8_comment: This one was over by half, as the absence-depleted Camo Toes were down 24-0 at the break.  Jamar W. had 2 TDs for Vegas in the first half while Captain Chris M. and Jared L. each had their own first half TD.  The second half was a bit more balanced as each team scored once - Jared gathered his 2nd TD of the game for Vegas and Andrew grabbed Camo's sole score on the day in the loss 31-6.
results_9_comment: The Twerkers grabbed their first victory in the icy lake bowl over the Enemies 25-18.  This game saw each team score 3 times a piece yet the Twerkers converted on all 3 of their XPs and Captain Jerrell P. ran back one of Slate's conversions for an extra 2 points.  The Slate were down 18-6 in the second half but made a game of it, tying the game at 18 all with about 5 minutes to go.  The Twerkers drove down and Jerrell grabbed his 2nd TD of the game as the winning score.  Larry W. account for 9 of the Twerkers points.  The Slate squad scored on two runs from QB Kyle M and a catch from Andy P. on 4th and goal.  Captain Kozak had the game's lone INT in the loss.
results_10_comment: The Teal team captured the first score in this contest off a score by Jarod T. and an XP conversion by Captain Jayme F.  Silver's Captain Joe H. had an INT but the Spooners were unable to convert, ending the first half down 7-0.   Silver opened the second half with a TD pass from QB John B. to Kevin K. and tied the game 7-7. The two teams then traded scores to be at 14 all with very little time left.  The Liminators drove the length of the field, running the clock down to the final play of the game, where reigning League MVP Dameron R. scored the game winner, 20-14.
results_11_comment: Purple and Navy arrived to find a wet field and the Plum Dumpsters came out victourious in the sludge-match. Clay A. and Craig N. did just enough to defeat an impressive debut for Mike C. and Tyler E. Navy has a lot of fresh meat but the ingredients are there for veteran Greg K. to cook up something special this season.
results_12_comment: This was an early season matchup of undefeated teams, as both teams won the first of their doubleheaders.  For Vegas, it was the Jamar W. show as he accounted for all 24 of Vegas's points.  For Royal, Miles S. equaled Jamar's output with 4 TDs of his own.  The difference in the game was two Royal XP conversions - 1 by Linda P. and one by Captain Brendan M, as Royal goes to 2-0 28-24 over Navy.

results_0_comment: Lime took a 8-6 lead into the half with Rob C and Justin P scoring a TD each for their teams.  The second half saw each team score twice with Lime holding off Maroon on the goalline for the last play of the game, as the 9 seed advances 20-18.
results_1_comment: In a 10 seed upset of a 5 (is this the NCAA tourney, with a 5 seed going down), Bluekakke defeated the Kilos 32-20 with Sean B., Brian D. and Adam R. getting first half TDs for Pacific and Brion having both first half TDs for Columbia.  Ray W. and Coach G finished up the scoring for Pacific in the second half, as they advanced over the Kilos.
results_2_comment: The Phite Club had their fight back in this one, with four first half TDs, 2 INTs and 1 sack, leading 25-12 over the Boehners.  Andy P. had 3 TDs and 2 sacks in the loss; Phite Club advanced 31-24.
results_3_comment: In a game much closer than the final scored indicated (Purple was up by 2 points in the second half), the Gang Violets put up 44 to advance.  Barry M. had 2 TDs and 2 XP conversions in the win.  White had scores from Jay A., Rudy L., Matt G. and Captain Josh R. in their final game on the season.
results_4_comment: The Gays started the playoffs with a bang, as Mike D. and Josh E. each had first half pick 6's, leading 33-0 at one point in the first half.  Royal fought back, scoring the final 22 points of the game but it was too little too late as Vegas advanced 33-22.
results_5_comment: The Butch Greens took a 14-6 lead into halftime but went scoreless in the second half, losing 18-14 to the Black squad.  Black held the Greens on a goalline stand to win the game by 4.  Trevor, Ryan and Charlie had Black's 3 scores in the victory.
results_6_comment: Fuchsia came out swinging with Jason and Sam having first half scores and Bill adding a first half INT, leading 14-0 at half.  DJ, Adam and Amanda all scored for Lime in the second half, but it wasn't enough, Lime's season ends 33-14.
results_7_comment: In a defensive battle, the Gang Violets won their second game of the day, beating Red 20-12.  Craig had 2 rushing TDs in the win while Matt M. and Jason W. did the scoring for Red in the loss.
results_8_comment: In one of the best games on the day, Gold squeaks out the victory 34-27.  Vegas took a 21-20 halftime lead off of scores by Greg, Robbie and Sparrow. Baxter had 2 first half TDs for Gold.  The second half saw Vegas holding a 27-26 lead with less than 1 minute to go and 4th and 10.  Gold's QB scampered for 10.5 yards to keep the drive alive and then went on to throw the game winning TD to Baxter, as Gold kept their Final Four hopes alive and kicking.
results_9_mvp: Kevin Kostyk (Dark Green), Adam Robbins (Pacific Blue)
results_9_comment: In a rare 2nd round game for a 10 seed, the Bluekakke held their own for the first half, down 18-14.  But you can only hold the number 1 scoring team in the league for so long, as Dark Green put up 32 total points to move on to the Quarterfinals.
results_10_comment: In one of their most complete games all season, the Squirts led 20-6 at the half with scores by Captain Adam S., QB Brandon W. and Jared L.  The second half saw INTs by Jared and Brandon, as they closed out Black's season 32-19.  Kyle, Trevor and Cole all scored for Black in the loss.
results_11_comment: Another game that was closer than the final score reflected, Navy led the Phite Club 19-18 at the half, with two first half TDs by Dameron.  Navy ran away with this on two back to back pick 6's, one by Will C. and the other by John W. to break it open.  AJ, Peter, Tony and Andrew had scores in the loss.
results_12_comment: This first half saw absolutely no defense, with a combined 53 points scored, as the Queens led 33-20.  The second half had 2 touchdowns by each team as the Queens kept their title quest alive, heading to the final four 48-32.  Captain Smiffy had 2 TDs in the loss.
results_13_comment: In a rematch of one of the best games of the regular season, which saw Leaf squeak out a win, this one was far from a mirror game.  The Gang Violets were playing their 3rd game of the day and it was obvious they were on fumes.  Leaf, meanwhile, executed a perfect game plan, as center Steve G. had catch after catch and last season's Offensive Player of the Year Larry W. came to life with 2 TDs and an INT. Leaf wins going away 31-12.
results_14_comment: This game got off to a rough start for the Tealers, as they took the first possession from their own 2 yard line and QB Brandon W. was sacked by Kyle S. for perhaps the league's first ever playoff safety, giving Navy a lead they'd never relinquish.  Navy led 28-12 at the half and never looked back.  John W. and Dameron split 6 TDs between then, while Captain Brian G. added one of his own in the victory.  Brad and Hobbs each had one TD and Charlie S. had 2 in the loss.
results_15_comment: Fuchsia's Clay A. kicked off this game with an INT off Gold's QB.  But Gold took a 2 point lead into the half, thanks to TDs by Tim, Marcus and Miles.  Z, Jack and Bill had Fuchsia's first half scores.  Tim and Miles added their second TDs of the second half, as Gold advances to the Final Four, the first one QB Matt P. will play in.
