results_4_mvp: MVPs: Jarod Trujillo (Dark Green), Cole Whitaker (Black)
results_0_comment: Chris M. and Mike D. each had a whopping 4 touchdowns for their teams. It ultimately came down to defense in this shootout so a combination of Brion S. (2 int's) and Sean S. (1 int and 2 second half TD's) gave Columbia Blue the victory heading into the playoffs.
results_1_comment: It was playoff's atmosphere already in this high stakes match up between the top teams in the Nellie's conference. On the line was a number one seed and an important double bye this weekend. Orange barely beat out Fuchsia to go 8-1 on the season and pushed Fuchsia to 6-3. Jack M. had 3 TD's and Jason C. added 3 sacks. Nikki M., Bill C. and Donald M. all had scores for Orange.
results_2_comment: Both Pacific and Teal were fighting to improve their playoff positions in the crowded standings. Staying true to their team names, Big Squirt Teal circled up and finished ontop of Pacific Bluekakke. Chris H., Adam S., Brandon W., Brad G., and Matt H. all contributed scores for Teal while Brian D. had the lone TD stat for Pacific.
results_3_comment: A battle of the rookie and the veteran QB. John B. had 3 scores and Alonzo M. had 1 score for Maroon. Gold had scores from Baxter O., Miles S. Marcus S. and Matt P. Experience won this time but Daniel H. has come full circle in his rookie season at QB and proved it by throwing the same amount of TD's as the veteran Matt P.
results_4_comment: This was a case of the number 1 scoring office in the league going to work.  The Turtles put up 51 points (only the 2nd 50+ point game of the season), with Jarod T. having a season's worth of TDs (5) in this one game! Kevin K. added 2 TDs and 2 XPs on the day for Dark Green.  Black had scores by Ken G., Kyle M. and Cole in the loss, 51-19.
results_5_comment: Co-game of the week.  Came down to the wire, as any battle for a #1 seed should.  Captain Scott S. had 3 TDs on the day for Leaf as they emerged victorious over the Violets.  Mark H. had an INT, Steve G. had an XP and Ryan M. had a sack, all in the win.  Jerrell, Barry and Craig all split the 3 TDs for Purple, with Sean G. adding in a 2pt conversion and Howard and Craig coming up with INTs for purple in the narrow loss, 26-20.
results_6_comment: What parity we have this season!  The difference between a 3-6 Lime team and a 7-2 Navy squad came down to 1 score, with Navy slipping by Lime 32-25.  Dameron and Will C. split 4 TDs evenly, while John W. added in his own in the victory to propel them to the #2 seed in the Nellies conference.  Meanwhile, Lime spread the ball around with Adam M. catching a TD while the couple of Kurt and TJ shared 2 TDs in the loss.
results_7_mvp: MVPs: Keith Combs (Medium Green), Eduardo Cabrera (Graphite)
results_7_comment: The Phite Club struggled to score in this one without QB Tony S but fought on anyway, losing to the Greens 26-6.  Eduardo C. recorded a sack and got the MVP for the Club.  Keith C. littered the stat sheet for the Butch Greens, with a TD, an XP and 3 recorded sacks in the victory.
results_8_mvp: MVPs: Bryant Burnheimer (Royal), Brendan McFarland (Burnt Orange)
results_8_comment: This was a tight one at half (12-12) and all the way through, with Royal pulling the squeaker over the Burnt Orange squad 32-31.  Dane S. had 2 sacks in the victory, while Tyler F. recorded 3 TDs and Captain Brian H. caught 2 TDs.  Brendan M. and Andy P. split 4 TDs while Greg S. nabbed one of his own in the loss for the Boehners.
results_9_comment: Despite being down 23-12 at the half, 29-18 in the second half and despite being winless on the season thus far, White kept its composure and snatched this victory out of Red's hands, scoring the last 14 points of this game to win 32-29.  White had 4 INTs on the day, 2 by Rudy L., and one a piece by Matt G. and Jay A.  QB Kyle B. had 2 rushing TDs in the victory.  Brandon B. filled up the stat sheet in the loss, scoring a TD and an XP, having an INT and having a 2 point return on an XP INT.

results_0_comment: This was a barnburner of a game under the lights of Friday Night with two of the Nellies conference best teams going head to head.  It took every last play to decide the winner as the Rovers took a 13-7 lead into halftime and won the game on the last play, 25-19.  Red had a 19-7 lead in the second half with about 15 minutes to play but the Rear Admirals refused to go away.  Navy scored with less than a minute to go to tie the game but the Red team was able to drive the length of the field thanks to a long catch and run from BB and a short TD scamper on the game’s final play from QB Kyle M. for the game winner.  Will C. had an INT and a TD and John W. had an INT and 2 TDs for the Admirals in the loss.
results_1_comment: The Butch Greens came upon a tough Fuchsia team under the lights, going down 30-14 to the Michael J. Fox inspired Fuchsia team.  Jamar W. (happy bday!) had a pick 6 in the first half and Jeremy added a TD and a 2pt conversion for the Greens in the loss.  Jack and Bill had a TD each in the first half and Clay and QB Scott added one of their own in the second half as Fuchsia cruised.  Big game coming up next week for the Fuchsia squad.  Orange awaits!
results_2_comment: QB Craig N. threw an INT to Alex P. right out of the gate, but little else would go wrong in this one for the Gang, as they would take a 14-7 lead into halftime off of two QB rushing TDs and finish with a 33 point win, 46-13.  Barry had an INT and Jerrell, Howard and Dennis each added receiving touchdowns for the Purple team.  Craig finished with 3 rushing TDs and an INT.  For Burnt Orange, Jacob W. had both of their scores in the loss.
results_3_comment: White continued to get close to its first victory in this one, as Lime won 25-14 in the end.  QB Marvin had  2 rushing TDs, while TJ and Marcus each had a receiving TD to procure this victory.  QB Kyle and Jay A. had White’s two scores in the loss.
results_4_comment: A 1 point lead at the half turned into a 9 point victory for the Columbia Kilos, who won their 4th game on the season to pull even at .500.  Bugsy littered the scoreboard with 4 TDs and 2 XPs for the victorious Kilos, while the Phite Club had TDs by Captain BJ, the brothers Kniseley and Jake in the loss.
results_5_comment: In a game inspired by Wiz Khalifa (black & yellow, stay up with me), the Golden Receivers, thrilled to have their QB back, put up 38 against the Black squad, winning by 13.  Miles S. and Baxter B. split 4 first half TDs for Gold, while Ryan B. and Santos scored for Black in the first half.  Miles added his 3rd TD in the second half while Santos went down swinging (he’s already moved to Dallas!) with another TD and an INT in the second half, as Gold won 38-25.
results_6_comment: Maroon started off receiving, but they weren't passive nor were they on bottom at the end. Rob C. earned 2 TDs while Marlon D., Daniel H, and John B. each had 1 TD in the Brick's 7 point win against the Boehners.  However, Burnt Orange didn't give up and replied often and hard with TDs of their own: Brett C. had 2 TDs, Alex P. had one, and Brendan M. caught 1 another. In addition, Howard Chan proved he was a beast and earned his 4th recorded sack of the season.
results_7_comment: In the shoot-out between the Queens and Kilos, neither team could stop the other's offense until late in the first half.  After receiving the ball, Orange drove down with Nikki K. scoring the TD and Billy K. following up with the extra point.  Columbia replied with a QB run and extra point by Tyler Lacy, while Orange returned with a behind-the-back bobble TD by Patrick K. and another extra point by Billy K.  Donald M. thwarted Columbia's second drive with an INT.  Both teams stepped up the defense in the second half with INTs by Billy K. and Matt C. for the Queens and Nolan L. for Columbia.  B. Stokes and Bill C. had their team's respective TDs to end the game 20 - 13, Orange.
results_8_comment: The Gays took a 12-6 lead into halftime in this matchup of veteran QBs, each tossing an INT in the first half.  In the end, Vegas overwhelmed the Club, taking this one 32-12.  QB Dan C. had a first half rushing TD, while Mike D., Jay M., Robbie L. and Enrique added the other scores for Vegas.
results_9_comment: In a matchup of depleted clubs, the Big Squirt Tealers put up a League season high 57 points to defeat the Ninja Turtles by 33 points.  Captain Smiffy of the Turtles did all he could to keep this one close, scoring all 4 of the Turtles TDs.  Meanwhile, the Tealers squirted off points from every direction with Chris H. having 4 TDs, Brad G. having 2 TDs and 2 INTs, newcomer Joe M. adding a pick 6 and an XP.  John R. (aka the Red Panda), Joe H. and Captain Adam S. all got on the scoreboard with XPs as well.  Teal win 57-24.
results_10_comment: The surprising Brick Hard Maroon team, once looking helpless and lurking near the bottom of the Power Rankings, have clawed their way back to .500 on the season with a win against the depleted Bluekakke team.  3rd String QB Brian D. threw two TDs to Captain Ray in the loss, while Rob C. and John B. added two TDs each for the victorious Maroon team as Maroon wins 33-13.
results_11_comment: In the near upset of the day, the Royal Hoes took a 7-6 lead into half time over the conference leading O-leaf-ia Newton Johns, thanks to a TD and XP by Patrick M.  Royal was only able to muster one other score in the second half (Stephen T.) while Leaf came up with 2, one by QB Mark H., as Leaf held on to win 20-14.

results_0_comment: Black decked the whimpering Gang in the first half of this one, picking off Purple's QB 3 times (Kyle had 2, Captain Ken G. had 1) en route to a 20-0 halftime lead.  The Gang got its act together in the second half and came roaring back but TDs to Howard and Jerrell, along with a QB TD scamper weren't quite enough, as Black held off Purple 26-22 to get its 3rd win on the season.
results_1_comment: Navy rode a great first half to victory in this contest.  TDs to Dameron, Will C. and 2 to John W. keyed the Admirals first half route 28-6, with Kyle S. adding 3 sacks.  John W. added his 3rd TD in the second half, as Navy cruised 34-13 over the Greens.  Judson W. had 2 TDs in the loss.
results_2_comment: The first half of this one saw an even number of TDs and INTs, as Graphite had 1 TD and 1 INT, with Red scoring 2 times and giving the ball away twice but managing a 13-6 halftime lead.  The second half saw the INT total rise to 5, as each team gave the ball away one additional time.  Red wins 25-18; JP & Shealy each have a sack for the Rovers.
results_3_comment: Low scoring first halves seemed to be the theme of the early games, as these two were tied 6 all at the break.  Adam R. won his first game at QB as he led two second half TDs en route to a nailbiter 19-13 victory as the Boehner's last play heave came up just short.
results_4_comment: This was a tough defensive matchup with the Tealers taking a 12-0 lead into halftime thanks to TDs by Charlie S. and Jared L., as well as an INT by Jared L.  The second half was similar, with each team managing only 6 points each - the Johns off of a Dan H. TD at the end of the game and the Squirts off of Charlie S's second TD of the game.  Mark H. had 2 INTs in the loss.
results_5_comment: This battle of the top two teams in the Nellies conference lived up to the hype, as the Admirals eeked out a 27-20 victory over the previously undefeated Queens.  At the half it was all tied up 7-7, with Will C. having both an INT and the lone Navy TD and Steve A. having the lone TD on a long run for the Queens.  The second half saw Matt C. adding a TD and a sack and Billy K having a score in the loss for the Queens.  John. W., Dameron and Captain Brian G. each had a second half score for the victorious Navy squad as they held on to become the top seed in the conference going in to week 7.
results_6_comment: The Receivers were lacking a starting QB on Sunday, as their tough day began by getting blanked by the Turtles 45-0.  Jarod, Kevin and Chris R. each had 2 scores while Adam B added one of his own in this blowout victory.  And I've mentioned every single stat written down for Gold in this summary.  Look for it.
results_7_comment: The Johns came off their loss to Teal with one thing on their minds - Victory.  They took it to the Bluekakke team, blanking them 33-0 in the second half of their doubleheader.  Shawn had a score for the Leaf squad and Mark H. added his 3rd INT on the day, while Markco had a sack, 2 ints, 2 tds, all while sucking a blue lollipop in the victory.
results_8_comment: The Kilos held their own in this one despite missing a few players.  Andy had two first half TDs and an INT while Scott G. had 2 first half TDs to take a 20-13 lead into halftime for the Fuchsia team.  Scott added a third TD in the second half and Mike Z had what proved to be the winning score, as the Fuchsia squad held off the Kilos 33-25.
results_9_comment: I Know, White made this one close for most of the first half, staying on par with the Queens until a costly INT to Billy K allowed the Queens to take a two score lead into halftime, up 19-7.  The second half saw Donald M. catch 2 TDs and Billy K. adding his second TD as the Orange squad proved why they are one of the top teams in the league, winning this one 40-13.
results_10_comment: Royal took advantage of the Pearce-less Gold team, jumping out to a 20-0 halftime lead off of scores by Stephen T and two by Tyler Fox, who also added two first half INTs.  Baxter had a first half INT for Gold.  The second half saw Gold break its scoreless streak with Sam C. having a TD and Baxter adding the 2pt conversion in the loss, as Royal hoed down the Receivers 40-8.
results_11_mvp: John Berry (Maroon), Jarod Trujillo ( Dark Green)
results_11_comment: After slamming a depleted Gold team, the Turtles came into this game against the Bricks as heavy favorites.  Jarod, Smiffy and Jason B. all added first half TDs as the favorite Turtles went to script in the first half, taking a 18-12 lead into halftime.  Marlon had both a sack (really!) and a TD in the first half for Maroon.  In the second half, the underdog Maroon squad tighted up its defense, allowing only 1 score after halftime (a running TD to QB Jim C.) and managed 2 scores of its own to John B. and a running TD to QB Daniel H, as the Brick Hard club got its second win in a squeaker 25-24.
results_12_comment: In the last game to go final on the day, Lime took a 12-6 lead into halftime with scores from Justin P. and Marcus B.  Josh had all 3 scores for Vegas in the loss, as the QB Marvin W.'s XP proved to be the difference.  Lime gets back on track.

results_3_mvp: Andy Pratt (B. Orange); Jarod Trujillo (D. Green)
results_0_comment: The first half of this matchup was a defensive battle, with each team scoring only once and the Gays taking a 7-6 lead into half off of Enrique P.'s TD.  The second half was a much more offensive game as 5 total second half TDs were scored.  Enrique added his second TD while BB matched him with 2 in the loss 29-20.
results_1_comment: Graphite had a tough go of it in this game, falling backwards to the Fuchsia squad 40-12.  The first half saw Fuchsia hold Tony S. and crew scoreless as they took a 14-0 lead into halftime off a Pick 6 by QB Scott G.  The second half saw a burst of TDs from the Fuchsia team with Bill, Jason, Clay and Bihn all scoring, while Peter S. added a second half TD and INT in the loss.  Phite club comes out bruised.
results_2_comment: In the shocker of the day, the Pacific team, who only last week beat a previously unbeaten Gold squad, this week pulls the opposite and loses to a previously winless Royal squad 24-6.  The Hoes picked off Pacific QB Coach G 3 times, with Tyler F. grabbing two and Captain Brian H. grabbing one of his own en route to the blowout.
results_3_comment: The Gang rode out to a 28-6 halftime lead with QB Craig N. rushing for two TDs and Jerrell and Howard each catching one in the first half.  Newcomer John (welcome to DC!) had Hard's lone first half score.  In the second half, Maroon settled down a bit, with John adding his second score of the game and Rob C. adding one of his own in the losing effort 36-19.
results_4_comment: Turtle backup QB Matt N. kept the score close in this one, leading two first half scores as his team was down 19-13 at the half.  Burnt's Jacob W. had 2 first half TDs to ensure B.O. went into the half smelling good.  The second half was similarly close, with Burnt Orange pulling out the victory 32-26.  Andy P. had a TD, XP and a sack in the second half for the win.
results_5_comment: The one loss Admirals team continued its season roll, defeating White 40-26.  The first half saw Dameron, John W. and Sheerod all getting on the scorecard with TDs while Shannon had a sack.  The second half saw Dameron add 2 additional TDs to bring his day total to 3 with Captain Josh R. having two TDs of his own and an XP in the loss.
results_6_comment: Lime's lone first half highlight was an INT by Marvin W. as the Kilos took a 7-0 first half lead.  Unfortunately, the second half wasn't much different, as the Columbia team blanked Lime 26-0, Brion had 2 TDs and an INT in the victory.
results_7_comment: This game couldn't have been closer in the first half with each team scoring twice to end the half tied up at 13.  Kozak and Matt C. were the big Queens in the first half with a TD each and Jeremy S. and QB David S. having the Butch teams first half TDs.  The second half could not have been more different, as the Queens had 3 INTs and ran away with it, scoring 3 times to 0 in the second half, finishing off the Greens 34-13.
results_8_comment: The Tealers rode a 3 INT and 2 TD first half performance to a 12-0 first half lead, as Brad G. added a TD and an INT in the first half.  Charlie S. had a great second half with a TD, XP and a Pick 2 for the Squirts as they ran away with this one 27-12.  James S. and Cole W. had TDs for the Black team in the loss.
results_9_comment: In the matchup of the day, the Receivers with 1 loss on the season squeaked out a victory over previously unbeaten Leaf 26-25.  Larry W. had a circus catch for a TD in the second half for the Johns and Tim S. had 2 second half TDs for the Gold team, the last one coming very late in the game as the game winner.

results_0_comment: The Kniseley Brothers both made impact plays in the first half of this one with Charlie getting a TD and Chris grabbing an INT.  Peter S. also added a TD and INT of his own in the first half.  Graphite led 20-0 at the half.  Kody Silva had the lone TD for Lime as they came out of this one bruised and battered by the Phite Club.
results_1_comment: The Pacific team held the Receivers to a season low 6 point first half and a season low 24 point game total, as Bluekakke took a 20-6 halftime lead off of Michelle F's and Adam R.'s TDs along with Coach G's rushing TD.  Adam added his second TD in the second half along with an INT, as Pacific cruised to a 45-24 victory.  Miles Simpson had 3 TDs in the loss.
results_2_comment: The Boehners ruled this game with a heavy gavel, dominating the Tealers.  Long D. had a rushing TD and two passing TDs in the 1st half, as the Burnt Orange squad led 19-0 at the half.  The second half was much the same, with Moptop having two INTs and Alex adding one of his own as the Boehners won 32-6.  Jared L. had 2 INTs and John R. had 3 sacks and the lone TD for the Tealers, who fell to 2-3 on the season.
results_3_comment: The Gang struggled to score in this one without their QB Craig N.  The Turtles had no issues, leading 13-0 at the half off of 2 INTs by Jason B.  Kevin K. added two second half scores for the Turtles, as they shelled the Gang 32-6, with Barry M. having the Gang's only TD.
results_4_comment: A tale of two halves with two magical plays determining the outcome of the game.  The first half saw the Kilos, with their backup QB Sean Stern, start fast, taking a 19-0 lead into halftime.  Nolan had two first half INTs, with Bugsy and Levert (welcome back!) each adding one of their own.  The Greens got the shot in the arm they needed on the first play of the second half with Judson W. returning the opening kickoff for Butch's first score of the game.  The game went back and forth until a 4th down for the Greens turned into a miraculous catch by Jamar W. in the endzone for a game-tying TD with very little time left.  Jamar then had what appeared to be the game winning XP catch as well.  But backup QB Bugsy led the Kilos down the field, and with 2 plays remaining in the game, threw a pass to the back of the endzone where Andy L jumped as high as he could to bring the ball down in bounds.  Game over.  This thriller went to the Kilos 32-27.
results_5_comment: White looked like they Knew in the first half of this one, keeping it close under the direction of new QB Kyle B.  Vegas led at the half 12-7, with Captain Enrique P. and Josh E. each having a TD for the Gays.  The second half was a different story, with Brian S. having 2 INTs, one returned for a TD, as the Gay team ran away from White 33-13.  Andy Allen was the lone bright spot for the White squad in the second half, having a TD and an INT.
results_6_comment: In a battle of winless squads, it was Hard to doubt the Brick team after they carried a strong first half performance into the second half.  Maroon led 20-6 at the half with Daniel H. having a Pick 6.  The second half saw Maroon grab a second pick 6, as Trey P. ran one back, his second TD of the game.  Patrick M. added a second half TD for the Hoes in the loss 40-14.
results_7_comment: Black decked the Hoes, who have yet to figure out how to put it all together.  Black led 26-0 at the half off of 2 rushing TDs by QB Charlie L and two receiving TDs by Santos.  Santos added 2 first half INTs as well, with Ken Gr. adding his own.  The second half saw the Black team grab 4 additional INTs, one Matty P. turned into a pick 6, as black dominated 39-0.
results_8_comment: This was a one score game at the half with the Butches leading the Gays 21-14 off a Jeremy S. TD and a Judson W. TD.  The second half saw Jamar W. continue his impressive day with 2 TDs in a 34-20 victory.  The Gays Brian S. had 2 TDs as well, with newcomer Andrew W. grabbing a second half sack in the loss.
results_9_comment: In a game of two very good teams, the Rovers carried a 13-12 lead into halftime with QB Kyle M. rushing for a TD and throwing one to Jim R.  Bill C. had two first half rushing TDs for the Queens.  The second half saw Gabe A. come to life with an INT and a TD, as the Queens escaped 26-20 over Red, who fell 1 yard short on a potential tying TD.
results_10_comment: This was another tale of two halves with backup QB Jason C. leading the Fuchsia team on 3 first half scoring drives, one to Justin M (welcome back!) who also added a first half INT.  The second half, however, saw Fuchsia wishing to go Back to the First Half, as Navy's backup QB Pmac got into a groove, sustaining 3 TD drives, all leading to TDs to Dameron R.  John W. caught the game winning XP, as Navy pulled off the victory 26-25.
results_11_comment: Fresh off a 39-0 victory, the Black team ran into a tough set of Johns.  At the half the Johns led 20-6 off of two TDs by Ryan S and one by Captain Scott S.  The second half the Leaf team piled it on, with 4 TDs and 3 INTs, closing with Mark H's pick 6 for the victory 46-12.

results_0_mvp: Orange: Bill Cammas / Vegas: Tim Adams
results_2_mvp: Teal: Chris Hobbs / Maroon: Trey Phillips
results_3_mvp: Red: Brandon Benjamin / Fuchsia: Mike Z.
results_4_mvp: Purple: Sean Gard / Royal: Tyler Fox
results_0_comment: In the battle of the Queens versus the Gays, everyone knows a Big Queen beats your Average Gay every time, as the Queens won this one 39-26 on Friday night.  The Queens took a 20-12 lead into halftime with Nikki and Billy K catching TDs.  Mike D. and Tim A. had first half scores for the Gays. The second half saw Billy K add another TD to his resume, while Tim A. and Josh E. got on the board for the Gays in the loss.
results_1_comment: Tyler Lacy and crew darkened the White team under the lights of Friday Night Lights this past Friday.  B. Stokes had 2 TDs and an INT in the first half, with Chris Morse adding an XP and a sack, as the Kilos pounded the White team 14-0 at half.  The second half was much the same, with Captain Sean Stern adding 2 second half INTs in the victory.
results_2_comment: Fuchsia held this one close in the first half without their starting QB, as backup Jason Clevenger thru a TD to Mike Z and ran an XP in.  The difference in the first half was a pick 6 by the Roving BB, as Red led 14-7 at the half.  The second half saw Ryan and BB score TDs for the Reds, as they won this battle by 2 scores, 27-13.
results_3_comment: The Gang rode the Hoes to a 24-0 first half lead, with Sean G. and Craig each adding a TD and Jerrell catching 2 in the first half.  The second half went to Royal, with Tyler scoring 2 TDs but the game was long over before then.  Purple doubles up Royal 40-20.
results_4_comment: The Tealers squirted through the Bricks in this one, with QB Brandon W. throwing for 7 TDs, 3 to MVP Chris Hobbs as he had a couple of SportsCenter-type catches.  Maroon played hard, giving it their all until the end, with Trey Phillips scoring its TD.
results_5_mvp: Leaf: Mike Benjamin / Dark: Andrew Carr
results_5_comment: Lime felt for the first time what victory tasted like as the Rovers just couldn't send enough over to remain unbeaten on the season.  Lime led this one at half 14-0 on Justin's and Marcus's scores.  Then Red roared back with a TD by Matt and two rushing TDs by Kyle McKinney, only to come up short in the end 22-20.
results_6_mvp: Lime: Justin Parker / Red: Matt Murtaugh
results_6_comment: In a early battle of unbeatens, the Newton-Johns said their own "Cowabungas" in beating the Turtles by 2 points.  Trainwreck (D. Green) and Mike Ben. (Leaf) had the two first half TDs, with Steve "I never get thrown to" Gong getting a second half TD for Leaf and Kevin K. doing all the scoring for Captain-less Turtles in the second half.  Leaf remains unbeaten on the season.
results_7_mvp: Pacific: Peter Pawlowski / Black: Cole Whittaker
results_7_comment: The first half scoresheet looks almost like it did before the game started, with the Greens having the lone first half points coming on Jeremy's TD, leading 6-0 at the half.  Justin did all he could in the second half for Lime, scoring once and having big catch after big catch in Lime's 20-8 loss.  Captain Kody's TD was called back on a jumping penalty, which was caught on camera and is in the weekly video.  Is it a jump?  YouDecide2014.
results_8_mvp: Medium: David Schilling / Lime: Justin Parker
results_8_comment: Gold continued its run of high scoring games, racking up 46 points with 26 coming in the first half as Sam C. scored twice and Mike Hess and Miles scoring once a piece in the first half.  Miles added a second TD in the second half and Sam C. added a third while Baxter got in on the action with a second half TD of his own.  Moptop scored the lone second half TD for the B.O. team in the loss 46-19.
results_9_mvp: Gold: Baxter O'Brien / B. Orange: Jacob Willis
results_9_comment: Black led the way over winless Pacific at the half 18-12 with Coleton, Ken and Trevor each having first half scores for the Black team.  But the second half was a different story as the Bluekakke decked the Black team, with Coach G scoring the winning TD with his legs.  Bluekakke wins its first game of the season 25-24.
results_10_mvp: Graphite: Tony Stewart / Navy: Sheerod Wilkerson
results_10_comment: The Navy Admirals tried to Phite the Club a bit shorthanded and lost.  Phite's Nick C. had 2 first half TDs with Tony, Peter and AJ adding second half scores in route to a 40-13 victory.  Bringing up the Rear, the Admirals Brian G. and QB Sheerod each had scores in the loss.

results_3_mvp: Teal: Chris Hobbs  /  Gold: Matt Pearce
results_4_mvp: Lime: Marvin Washington / Orange: Nikki Kasparek
results_0_comment: This was a back and forth game that pretty much hinged on an early interception by Andrew Carr for the Turtles.  He lept out of his shell and caught Hoes' QB Scott Kisha's INT on Royal's first drive of the game.  The Turtles won 34-20.
results_1_comment: Brick Hard ran into a tough team full of Johns on Friday Night with QB Daniel Honeycutt making his DCGFFL QB debut in the loss.  He did have one bright spot, as he picked off Leaf QB Mark Hofberg's pass and took it to the house to give Maroon it's lone score as Leaf won big 44-6.
results_2_comment: This game featured 6 INTs spread amongst both teams. White was only down 12-6 at the half.  Then the Club started Phiting hardcore and pulled away to win by 23, with two second half TDs from Jake.
results_3_comment: In the highest scoring game of the season so far, the Receivers came up with a 4 point victory.  After being down by 14 at the half and by 2 points with less than a minute to go, QB Matt Pearce engineered a victory.  Baxter O'Brien caught the go-ahead TD pass on the next to last play of the game to sink the Tealers.
results_4_comment: Lime took a 16-13 lead into halftime off TJ Rhone and Marcus Boyce TDs.  The Queens bounced back in the second half with Nikki having both 2nd half TDs, as the Queens kept the Lime team winless on the season.
results_5_mvp: Fuchsia: Scott Graham / White: Linda Pratt
results_5_comment: Boehner got his first victory of the congressional season, as MopTop led the Burnt Orange squad with a second half TD and INT.  Santos had two second half TDs as his Black team found themselves decked 30-20.
results_6_mvp: Teal: Chris Hobbs / Purple: Howard Yuan
results_6_comment: The Tealers had little left to squirt in this game, losing in blowout fashion 43-14.  The backbreaker was a 50 yard run by QB Craig Neiswanger on the last play of the half to put the Violets up by 2 scores.  That trend would continue throughout the game as the Gang ran over the Tealers.
results_7_mvp: Black: James Santos / B. Orange: Howard Chan
results_7_comment: Fuchsia stayed undefeated in this defensive battle 18-8. Clay Arnold added an INT and Scott Graham caught two to keep Fuchsia's perfect record in tack.  Linda P. had White's lone score.
results_8_mvp: Red: Brandon Benjamin / Medium Green: Jeremy Steslicki
results_8_comment: The pinky-less David Schilling held his own in this Christmas bowl, throwing a couple of TDs to Jeremy Steslicki.  But the Rovers were just too much, as BB scored 3 TDs in this one to carry them to a 5 point victory and a 2-0 start.
results_9_mvp: Fuchsia:  Jack Miles / Vegas Gold: Josh Ellis
results_9_comment: The Kilos ran into a strong Rear in this one, as Sheerod tossed for 6 TDs and added a pick 6.  The Admirals win 46-14.
results_10_mvp: Purple: Howard Yuan / Pacific: Sam Shelton
results_10_comment: The drag show didn't drag in this first half, as Mike Zgoda led the way for Fuchia with 2 TDs and Fuchsia took a commanding lead into halftime. The Gays would make a second half run of it, with Mike D. and Robbie Ladd each adding a score, but alas, the Gays were on their knees at the end of this one 31-23.
results_11_mvp: Columbia: Nola Lazarus / Navy: Sheerod Wilkerson
results_11_comment: The Gang relied upon their staunch defense, taking a 14-0 lead into halftime with Sean and Howard each having scores.  The second half was an even affair, with both teams coming up with 2 TDS - Purple's going to Howard, giving him 3 for the game - as the Gang did what they normally do at a Bluekakke.

results_0_mvp: Vegas: Mike D'Ignazio  /  Navy: Porter Brockway
results_1_mvp: Pacific Blue: Sam Smallwood  /  Dark Green: Kevin Smiffy
results_2_mvp: Maroon: Trey Phillips  /  Black: Cole Whitaker
results_3_mvp: Leaf: Mark Hofberg  /  Burnt Orange: Brendan McFarland
results_4_mvp: Purple: Jerrell Price  /  Gold: Baxter O'Brien
results_0_comment: A solid debut by the Rear Admirals who led most of the way, up 13-12 at the half.  Captain Brian Golden had his first DCGFFL TD catch in the first half.  Porter B. added a pick 6 to his resume in the second half.  Mike D. had 2 TDs in the loss.
results_1_comment: This was a battle from the beginning.  Ninja Turtles' QB Jim Connolly started his season with a first-pass INT to Adam Robbins.  Unfortunately for the Bluekakke, Coach G started his season in similar fashion with the first two passes of this game being INTs.  Smiffy turned back the clock with a 4TD performance in the win.  Sam Smallwood had a chance to score the tying TD on the penultimate play of the game with a beautiful 70 yard pass from Coach G, but the pass needed to be 69 yards.  Bluekakke takes it all over the face in this one.
results_2_comment: In this battle of first time QBs, Black's QB Charlie Lingafelt looked strong with a 4 TD performance.  Marlon D. (Maroon's backup QB) figured out how hard it is to QB in this league in the first half of the game.  But he was able to recover, tossing 2 TDs in the second half.  Newcomer Alonzo Mable came down with 2 TDs and an INT in his DCGFFL debut.
results_3_comment: Leaf started off fast, going up 26-0 at the half with lots of players getting involved, including a sensational catch by captain Scott Steinhardt.  The Boehners finally got some offense going in the second half with MopTop grabbing 2 TDs and LA Returner Mark Martinez added in a second half sack.
results_4_comment: Howard Y. started his last DCGFFL season with a bang, scoring Purple's first TD of the season.  Jerrell (welcome back!) and Ali added the other two scores for the Gang.  And Sean G. sacked his hard-to-sack good friend Matt P in the first half.  Mike Hess, Baxter and Sam all filled up the stat sheet with scores for the Receivers in the victory.
results_5_mvp: Columbia Blue: B. Stokes  /  Red: Jason Weaver
results_5_comment: Red Rover is happy BB came over.  He led the way with 2 TDs and an INT.  After being down 7-0 to start the game, the Rover's Jason W. had a 40 yard TD catch and WTF added a 2pt conversion from QB Kyle McKinney to give them a lead they'd never relinquish.  Newcomer QB Tyler L. held his own, scoring 20 in his first game.
results_6_mvp: Teal: Jared Lucas  /  Royal: Stephen Tackney
results_6_comment: Very close game throughout, with the largest lead of the game being a 5 point lead by Teal half way through the second half.  Newcomers Billy Lechert (1) and Jared Lucas (2) had scores for the Squirts along with Charlie Salem (1).  Stephen Tackney (2) and Dane Snowden (1) tore it up for Royal.  Teal pulled off the victory 25-21.
results_7_mvp: Fuchsia: Clay Arnold  /  Lime: T.J. Rhone
results_7_comment: It felt like the first time lime had played together (oh wait, it was!).  At the half, however, Lime was holding their own, up 8-6.  But the second half started off with a TD to Jack Miles (who followed that up with 2 others as well) and the rout was on.
results_8_mvp: Medium Green: David Schilling  /  White: B. Neal
results_8_comment: Welcome back to the league JB!  QB JB tried to run an offense with 6 receivers and no blocking but Butch Keith Combs told him, "No, sir" as he was on the QB practically when he got the ball in his hands on every play.  David Schilling used his one play to perfection, throwing for 5 TDs and catching two of JB's INTs.
results_9_mvp: Graphite: Sam Benton  /  Orange:  Patrick Kozak
results_9_comment: The battle of the BFs ended with both winning MVP but only one coming away a winner, as Kozak's Queens fought off the Sam Benton and the rest of his Phite Club 35-12.  Kozak and Matt C. both had two TDs while Nick C. and Sam B. had TDs for the Club in the loss.
